%3EIn%20a%20significant%20diplomatic%20move%2C%20India%20has%20spearheaded%20recommendations%20for%20Canada%20to%20fortify%20measures%20preventing%20attacks%20on%20worship%20places%20and%20effectively%20address%20hate%20speech.%20The%20proposals%20were%20presented%20during%20the%20UN%20Human%20Rights%20Council%20Review%20meeting%2C%20where%20diplomats%20from%20India%2C%20Bangladesh%2C%20and%20Sri%20Lanka%20shared%20their%20insights%20and%20recommendations.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIndian%20diplomat%20Mohammed%20Hussain%20noted%20legislative%20enactments%20such%20as%20the%20National%20Housing%20Strategy%20Act%20and%20the%20Accessible%20Canada%20Act%20while%20addressing%20the%20issue%20at%20the%20Council%20meeting.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20note%20the%20enactment%20of%20the%20National%20Housing%20Strategy%20Act%2C%20Accessible%20Canada%20act%2C%20and%20National%20strategy%20to%20combat%20human%20trafficking%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Hussain%20addressing%20the%20UNHRC%20review%20meeting.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIndia%20also%20recommended%20that%20Canada%20strengthen%20its%20domestic%20framework%20to%20prevent%20the%20misuse%20of%20freedom%20of%20expression%2C%20particularly%20for%20inciting%20violence.%20Additionally%2C%20India%20urged%20Canada%20to%20disallow%20activities%20of%20groups%20promoting%20extremism%2C%20prevent%20attacks%20on%20places%20of%20worship%20of%20religious%20and%20racial%20minorities%2C%20and%20enhance%20measures%20to%20address%20hate%20crimes%20and%20hate%20speech.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIndia%20recommends%20the%20following%20to%20Canada%20-%20further%2C%20strengthen%20the%20domestic%20framework%20to%20prevent%20misuse%20of%20freedom%20of%20expression%2C%20for%20inciting%20violence%20and%20disallow%20activities%20of%20groups%20that%20are%20promoting%20extremism%3B%20effectively%20prevent%20attacks%20on%20places%20of%20worship%20of%20religious%20and%20racial%20minorities%2C%20strengthen%20legislative%20and%20other%20measures%20to%20address%20hate%20crimes%20and%20hate%20speech%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20also%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBangladesh%20diplomat%20Abdullah%20Al%20Forhad%20commended%20Canada's%20progress%20in%20human%20rights%20protection%20and%20acknowledged%20the%20ongoing%20implementation%20of%20its%20strategy%20to%20combat%20human%20trafficking.%20However%2C%20Bangladesh%20recommended%20that%20Canada%20intensify%20efforts%20against%20racism%2C%20hate%20speech%2C%20hate%20crimes%2C%20and%20discrimination%20against%20migrants%20and%20Muslim%20minorities.%20They%20also%20called%20for%20measures%20to%20reduce%20carbon%20emissions%20and%20urged%20international%20cooperation%20in%20addressing%20climate%20change%20impacts.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIn%20spite%20of%20cooperation%2C%20Bangladesh%20offers%20recommendations%20to%20Canada%3A%20intensify%20its%20efforts%20to%20combat%20racism%2C%20hate%20speech%2C%20hate%20crimes%2C%20and%20discrimination%20against%20migrants%20and%20Muslim%20minorities%2C%20take%20necessary%20measures%20to%20reduce%20carbon%20emissions%3B%20strengthen%20international%20cooperation%20in%20addressing%20the%20negative%20impacts%20of%20climate%20change%3B%20and%20consider%20ratifying%20an%20international%20convention%20on%20the%20protection%20of%20the%20rights%20of%20all%20migrants%2C%20workers%20and%20members%20of%20their%20families%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Bangladesh's%20Al%20Forhad.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMeanwhile%2C%20Sri%20Lankan%20diplomat%20Thilini%20Jayasekara%20also%20recommended%20Canada%20accede%20to%20the%20Convention%20on%20the%20Protection%20of%20Rights%20of%20All%20Migrant%20Workers%2C%20take%20measures%20against%20racial%20discrimination%20affecting%20immigrants'%20rights%2C%20counter%20misinformation%20against%20minority%20communities%2C%20and%20strengthen%20its%20national%20mechanism%20for%20comprehensive%20reporting%20and%20follow-up%20on%20international%20human%20rights%20recommendations.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BSri%20Lanka%20welcomes%20the%20cooperation%20extended%20by%20the%20Government%20of%20Canada%20during%20the%20visit%20of%20UN%20Special%20Rapporters%20on%20contemporary%20forms%20of%20slavery%20and%20on%20the%20rights%20of%20Indigenous%20people.%20Sri%20Lanka%20recommends%20Canada%20to%20one%2C%20accede%20to%20the%20Convention%20on%20the%20Protection%20of%20Rights%20of%20All%20Migrant%20workers%20and%20members%20of%20their%20families.%20Two%2C%20continue%20to%20take%20measures%20against%20racial%20discrimination%2C%20in%20particular%20to%20avoid%20discriminatory%20policies%20and%20regulations%20affecting%20the%20rights%20of%20immigrants%2C%20including%20in%20the%20area%20of%20health%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20the%20Sri%20Lankan%20diplomat.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThree%2C%20continue%20to%20take%20measures%20to%20counter%20misinformation%20against%20minority%20communities.%20Four%2C%20strengthen%20its%20national%20mechanism%20for%20comprehensive%20reporting%20and%20follow%20up%20in%20relation%20to%20recommendations%20received%20from%20international%20human%20rights%20mechanisms%20and%20treaty%20obligations.%20We%20wish%20Canada%20success%20in%20its%20UPR%20engagement%2C%26quot%3B%20Thilini%20Jayasekara%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ECanadian%20PM%20Justin%20Trudeau%20introduced%20a%20fresh%20sour%20note%20in%20bilateral%20ties%20with%20India%20amid%20the%20continuing%20diplomatic%20standoff%2C%20affirming%20his%20earlier%20claim%20of%20Indian%20involvement%20in%20the%20killing%20of%20Khalistani%20terrorist%20Hardeep%20Singh%20Nijjar.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEarlier%20on%20Saturday%2C%20Canadian%20PM%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fjustin-trudeau-hardeep-singh-nijjar-india-canada-ties-if-bigger-countries-trudeaus-fresh-barb-at-india-amid-diplomatic-row-4568475%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EJustin%20Trudeau%20accused%20New%20Delhi%20of%20violating%20the%20Vienna%20Convention%3C%2Fa%3E%20by%20%26quot%3Bkicking%20out%26quot%3B%2040%20diplomats%20at%20a%20time%20when%20his%20count