A%2F%2Fwww.science.org%2Fdoi%2F10.1126%2Fsciadv.adj2457%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Epotential%20mechanism%3C%2Fa%3E%20explaining%20how%20these%20distinctive%20patterns%20form%20%E2%80%93%20that%20could%20potentially%20be%20applied%20to%20medical%20diagnostics%20and%20synthetic%20materials.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20thought%20experiment%20can%20help%20visualize%20the%20challenge%20of%20achieving%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhy-zebras-have-stripes-2014-3%5C%22%3Edistinctive%20color%20patterns%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Imagine%20gently%20adding%20a%20drop%20of%20blue%20and%20red%20dye%20to%20a%20cup%20of%20water.%20The%20drops%20will%20slowly%20disperse%20throughout%20the%20water%20due%20to%20the%20process%20of%20diffusion%2C%20where%20molecules%20move%20from%20an%20area%20of%20higher%20concentration%20to%20lower%20concentration.%20Eventually%2C%20the%20water%20will%20have%20an%20even%20concentration%20of%20blue%20and%20red%20dyes%20and%20become%20purple.%20Thus%2C%20diffusion%20tends%20to%20create%20color%20uniformity.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20question%20naturally%20arises%3A%20How%20can%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.insider.com%2Fviral-tiktok-woman-unknowingly-holding-venomous-blue-ringed-octopus-dangerous-2021-3%5C%22%3Edistinct%20color%20patterns%3C%2Fa%3E%20form%20in%20the%20presence%20of%20diffusion%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EMovement%20and%20boundaries%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EMathematician%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Falan-turing-notes-found-at-bletchley-park-2015-2%5C%22%3EAlan%20Turing%3C%2Fa%3E%20first%20addressed%20this%20question%20in%20his%20seminal%201952%20paper%2C%20%26quot%3B%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdoi.org%2F10.1098%2Frstb.1952.0012%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EThe%20Chemical%20Basis%20of%20Morphogenesis%3C%2Fa%3E.%26quot%3B%20Turing%20showed%20that%20under%20appropriate%20conditions%2C%20the%20chemical%20reactions%20involved%20in%20producing%20color%20can%20interact%20with%20each%20other%20in%20a%20way%20that%20counteracts%20diffusion.%20This%20makes%20it%20possible%20for%20colors%20to%20self-organize%20and%20create%20interconnected%20regions%20with%20different%20colors%2C%20forming%20what%20are%20now%20called%20Turing%20patterns.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20in%20mathematical%20models%2C%20the%20boundaries%20between%20color%20regions%20are%20fuzzy%20due%20to%20diffusion.%20This%20is%20unlike%20in%20nature%2C%20where%20boundaries%20are%20often%20sharp%20and%20colors%20are%20well%20separated.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221621%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20brown%20whitemouth%20moray%20(Gymnothorax%20meleagris)%20with%20white%20spots%20emerges%20from%20a%20rock%20underwater%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F655256f658cf5fbccb9594c6%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221215%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EMany%20marine%20animals%20have%20patterns%20to%20help%20them%20blend%20in%20with%20the%20underwater%20environment.%3Cp%3EHUM%20Images%2FUniversal%20Images%20Group%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EOur%20team%20thought%20a%20clue%20to%20figuring%20out%20how%20animals%20create%20distinctive%20color%20patterns%20could%20be%20found%20in%20lab%20experiments%20on%20micron-sized%20particles%2C%20such%20as%20the%20cells%20involved%20in%20producing%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-squid-octopus-skin-camouflage-works-2015-9%5C%22%3Ecolors%20of%20an%20animal's%20skin%3C%2Fa%3E.%20My%20work%20and%20work%20from%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdoi.org%2F10.1073%2Fpnas.1511484112%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eother%20labs%3C%2Fa%3E%20found%20that%20micron-sized%20particles%20form%20banded%20structures%20when%20placed%20between%20a%20region%20with%20a%20high%20concentration%20of%20other%20dissolved%20solutes%20and%20a%20region%20with%20a%20low%20concentration%20of%20other%20dissolved%20solutes.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20context%20of%20our%20thought%20experiment%2C%20changes%20in%20the%20concentration%20of%20blue%20and%20red%20dyes%20in%20water%20can%20propel%20other%20particles%20in%20the%20liquid%20to%20move%20in%20certain%20directions.%20As%20the%20red%20dye%20moves%20into%20an%20area%20where%20it%20is%20at%20a%20lower%20concentration%2C%20nearby%20particles%20will%20be%20carried%20along%20with%20it.%20This%20phenomenon%20is%20called%20diffusiophoresis.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EYou%20benefit%20from%20diffusiophoresis%20whenever%20you%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.insider.com%2Fguides%2Fhome%2Fhow-much-laundry-detergent-to-use%5C%22%3Edo%20your%20laundry%3C%2Fa%3E%3A%20Dirt%20particles%20move%20away%20from%20your%20clothing%20as%20soap%20molecules%20diffuse%20out%20from%20your%20shirt%20and%20into%20the%20water.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EDrawing%20sharp%20boundaries%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20wondered%20whether%20Turing%20patterns%20composed%20of%20regions%20of%20concentration%20differences%20could%20also%20move%20micron-sized%20particles.%20If%20so%2C%20would%20the%20resulting%20patterns%20from%20these%20particles%20be%20sharp%20and%20not%20fuzzy%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETo%20answer%20this%20question%2C%20we%20conducted%20computer%20simulations%20of%20Turing%20patterns%20%E2%80%94%20including%20hexagons%2C%20stripes%2C%20and%20double%20spots%20%E2%80%94%20and%20found%20that%20diffusiophoresis%20makes%20the%20resulting%20patterns%20significantly%20more%20distinctive%20in%20all%20cases.%20These%20diffusiophoresis%20simulations%20were%20able%20to%20replicate%20the%20intricate%20patterns%20on%20the%20skin%20of%20the%20ornate%20boxfish%20and%20jewel%20moray%20eel%2C%20which%20isn't%20possible%20through%20Turing's%20theory%20alone.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%20data-embed-type%3D%5C%22youtube%5C%22%20data-type%3D%5C%22embed%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Ciframe%20width%3D%5C%22560%5C%22%20allowfullscreen%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.youtube.com%2Fembed%2FpU-EB6fa0As%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22315%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fiframe%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cp%3EFurther%20supporting%20our%20hypothesis%2C%20our%20model%20was%20able%20to%20reproduce%20the%20findings%20of%20a%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdoi.org%2F10.1038%2Fs41567-021-01213-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Elab%20study%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%20how%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbiologists-extract-e-coli-genetic-code-from-16th-century-mummy-2022-6%5C%22%3Ebacterium%20%3Cem%3EE.%20coli%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20moves%20molecular%20cargo%20within%20themselves.%20Diffusiophoresis%20resulted%20in%20sharper%20movement%20patterns%2C%20confirming%20its%20role%20as%20a%20physical%20mechanism%20behind%20biological%20pattern%20formation.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBecause%20the%20cells%20that%20produce%20the%20pigments%20that%20make%20up%20the%20colors%20of%20an%20animal's%20skin%20are%20also%20micron-sized%2C%20our%20findings%20suggest%20that%20diffusiophoresis%20may%20play%20a%20key%20role%20in%20creating%20distinctive%20color%20patterns%20more%20broadly%20in%20nature.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3ELearning%20nature's%20trick%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EUnderstanding%20how%20nature%20programs%20specific%20functions%20can%20help%20researchers%20design%20synthetic%20systems%20that%20perform%20similar%20tasks.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELab%20experiments%20have%20shown%20that%20scientists%20can%20use%20diffusiophoresis%20to%20create%20membrane-less%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.insider.com%2Fwater-filter-mistakes-increase-risk-bacterial-infection-2021-8%5C%22%3Ewater%20filters%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20low-cost%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Famazon-machine-learning-ai-drug-discovery-clinical-trials-deepmind-google-2022-10%5C%22%3Edrug%20development%20tools%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOur%20work%20suggests%20that%20combining%20the%20conditions%20that%20form%20Turing%20patterns%20with%20diffusiophoresis%20could%20also%20form%20the%20basis%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%2