g-gone%20former%20captain%2C%20it%E2%80%99s%20usually%20a%20sign%20of%20desperation.%20And%20it%20doesn%E2%80%99t%20often%20lead%20to%20victory.%20It%20could%2C%20just%20could%2C%20be%20a%20masterstroke.%20More%20often%2C%20however%20well%20regarded%20the%20hero%20of%20yesteryear%20may%20be%2C%20he%20usually%20succeeds%20only%20in%20showing%20why%20everyone%20thought%20his%20innings%20was%20long%20over.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20return%20of%20David%20Cameron%20to%20the%20top%20rank%20of%20politics%20seven%20years%20after%20he%20stepped%20down%20as%20Prime%20Minister%20is%20one%20of%20those%20eye-rubbing%20moments.%20Can%20this%20really%20be%20happening%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20526px)%2085vw%2C%20526px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F04%2F20115409%2Funnamed.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22526%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F04%2F20115409%2Funnamed.jpg%20526w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F04%2F20115409%2Funnamed-247x300.jpg%20247w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-649461%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22640%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EIllustration%3A%20Pariplab%20Chakraborty%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ERishi%20Sunak%20has%20appointed%20Cameron%20to%20be%20Britain%E2%80%99s%20new%20foreign%20secretary%2C%20which%20will%20put%20him%20in%20charge%20of%20some%20of%20the%20biggest%20issues%20facing%20the%20government%3A%20its%20stand%20on%20the%20Israel-Gaza%20conflict%3B%20how%20to%20support%20Ukraine%20in%20its%20war%20with%20Russia%3B%20and%20improving%20relations%20with%20Britain%E2%80%99s%20nearest%20neighbours%2C%20which%20have%20never%20recovered%20from%20Brexit.%20Cameron%20is%20also%20seen%20as%20an%20advocate%20of%20engaging%20with%20China%20rather%20than%20keeping%20Beijing%20at%20a%20distance.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20his%20first%20comment%20after%20the%20appointment%2C%20Cameron%20described%20Rishi%20Sunak%20as%20a%20%E2%80%98strong%20and%20capable%E2%80%99%20leader%20and%20said%20he%20intended%20to%20%E2%80%98help%20him%20deliver%20the%20security%20and%20prosperity%20our%20country%20needs%E2%80%99.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDavid%20Cameron%20won%20two%20general%20elections%20for%20the%20Conservatives%20but%20stood%20down%20as%20prime%20minister%20after%20calling%2C%20and%20losing%2C%20the%20Brexit%20referendum%20on%20leaving%20the%20European%20Union%20in%202016.%20He%20promptly%20stepped%20back%20from%20political%20life%20and%20is%20no%20longer%20a%20Member%20of%20Parliament.%20To%20take%20up%20his%20new%20role%2C%20Cameron%20is%20being%20appointed%20to%20the%20unelected%20second%20chamber%20of%20Parliament%2C%20the%20House%20of%20Lords%20%E2%80%93%20it%E2%80%99s%20very%20unusual%20for%20one%20of%20the%20most%20senior%20roles%20in%20government%20to%20be%20held%20by%20someone%20in%20the%20House%20of%20Lords.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20is%20Rishi%20Sunak%E2%80%99s%20%E2%80%9Cback%20to%20the%20future%E2%80%9D%20moment.%20He%20is%20summoning%20a%20figure%20from%20the%20party%E2%80%99s%20past%20to%20try%20to%20improve%20its%20future%20prospects.%20He%20wants%20a%20cabinet%20which%20is%20united%20and%20loyal%20to%20him%20ahead%20of%20a%20general%20election%20expected%20in%20about%20a%20year%E2%80%99s%20time.%20If%20the%20opinion%20polls%20are%20borne%20out%2C%20Sunak%E2%80%99s%20Conservatives%20are%20heading%20to%20an%20abject%20defeat.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20cabinet%20reshuffle%20that%20has%20led%20to%20David%20Cameron%E2%80%99s%20political%20rebirth%20probably%20wasn%E2%80%99t%20long-planned.%20It%E2%80%99s%20a%20consequence%20of%20Sunak%E2%80%99s%20decision%20to%20sack%20another%20of%20his%20top%20team%2C%20the%20home%20secretary%2C%20Suella%20Braverman%2C%20for%20persistently%20going%20off-message%20in%20her%20public%20remarks.%20Her%20latest%20incendiary%20comments%20have%20been%20to%20denounce%20huge%20pro-Palestine%20protests%20in%20London%20as%20%E2%80%98hate%20marches%E2%80%99%20and%20to%20accuse%20London%E2%80%99s%20police%20of%20political%20bias%20in%20the%20way%20they%20deal%20with%20these%20demonstrations.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBraverman%20had%20become%20a%20liability.%20Her%20comments%20last%20week%20clearly%20undermined%20confidence%20in%20the%20police%20%E2%80%93%20exactly%20the%20opposite%20of%20what%20you%20would%20expect%20a%20home%20secretary%2C%20the%20minister%20in%20charge%20of%20law%20and%20order%2C%20to%20do.%20She%20accused%20London%E2%80%99s%20police%20of%20left-wing%20bias%20in%20dealing%20with%20protests%20demanding%20a%20ceasefire%20in%20Gaza%20and%20publicly%20%E2%80%93%20but%20unsuccessfully%20%E2%80%93%20urged%20the%20police%20to%20ban%20the%20most%20recent%20march%20on%20Saturday%20which%20was%20attended%20by%20half-a-million%20or%20so%20people.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESuella%20Braverman%20has%20form%20when%20it%20comes%20to%20eye-catching%20and%20deeply%20illiberal%20remarks%3A%20she%20has%20described%20the%20flow%20of%20illegal%20immigrants%20crossing%20the%20Channel%20in%20small%20boats%20as%20an%20invasion%3B%20she%20has%20championed%20the%20bizarre%20scheme%20to%20offload%20some%20of%20these%20illegal%20immigrants%20to%20Rwanda%20in%20central%20Africa%3B%20she%20recently%20said%20that%20some%20of%20the%20homeless%2C%20camping%20on%20city%20centre%20pavements%20in%20cheap%2C%20tiny%20tents%2C%20had%20made%20a%20lifestyle%20choice%2C%20suggesting%20that%E2%80%99s%20the%20way%20they%20wanted%20to%20live.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhy%20has%20Braverman%20made%20such%20a%20string%20of%20inflammatory%20comments%3F%20Well%2C%20probably%20because%20she%20really%20believes%20what%20she%E2%80%99s%20saying.%20She%20is%20on%20the%20right%20wing%20of%20the%20Conservative%20Party%2C%20a%20determined%20Brexiteer%2C%20who%20believes%20in%20a%20smaller%20state%2C%20lower%20taxes%2C%20and%20putting%20Britain%20and%20the%20British%20first.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20there%E2%80%99s%20more%20to%20it.%20She%20is%20also%20campaigning%20for%20her%20next%20job.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBraverman%20has%20already%20run%20once%20for%20leader%20of%20the%20Conservative%20Party%20and%20did%20better%20than%20expected.%20She%20is%20positioning%20herself%20to%20be%20the%20right-wing%20candidate%20for%20party%20leader%20whenever%20there%20is%20a%20vacancy.%20If%20Sunak%20loses%20the%20next%20general%20election%2C%20he%20will%20probably%20stand%20down%20as%20Conservative%20leader.%20And%20given%20the%20right-wing%20fervour%20among%20the%20Conservative%20rank-and-file%2C%20who%20make%20the%20final%20choice%2C%20she%20stands%20a%20fair%20chance%20of%20replacing%20him%20as%20leader.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESuella%20Braverman%20%E2%80%93%20born%20Sue-Ellen%20Fernandes%20%E2%80%93%20has%20an%20interesting%20backstory.%20Her%20parents%20are%20from%20Africa%20(Kenya%20and%20Mauritius)%20and%20of%20Indian%20ancestry.%20Her%20father%20is%20a%20Christian%20of%20Goan%20heritage%3B%20her%20mother%20has%20a%20Tamil%20Hindu%20background.%20Braverman%20is%20a%20Cambridge-educated%20barrister%2C%20and%20a%20member%20of%20the%20Triratna%20Buddhist%20community.%20Her%20husband%20is%20Jewish.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20well%20as%20being%20of%20Indian%20heritage%2C%20Braverman%20has%20something%20else%20in%20common%20with%20Rishi%20Sunak.%20She%E2%80%99s%20young%20for%20someone%20reaching%20to%20top%20ranks%20of%20politics%20%E2%80%93%2043%2C%20and%20just%20a%20month%20older%20than%20the%20prime%20minister.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBy%20sacking%20Braverman%2C%20Sunak%20has%20sought%20to%20establish%20his%20authority%20over%20a%20fractious%20cabinet.%20And%20in%20bringing%20back%20David%20Cameron%2C%20Sunak%20has%20turned%20to%20an%20experienced%20colleague%20who%20he%20can%20be%20confident%20is%20not%20conspiring%20to%20take%20his%20job.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1699878727000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2016%2F04%2FPrime_Minister_David_Cameron_speaking_at_the_opening_of_the_GAVI_Alliance_immunisations_pledging_conference_2.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fworld%2Flondon-calling-why-sunak-called-the-old-captain-back-to-the-crease%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Rishi%20Sunak%20has%20appointed%20former%20Prime%20Minister%20David%20Cameron%20to%20be%20Britain%E2%80%99s%20new%20foreign%20secretary%2C%20which%20will%20put%20him%20in%20charge%20of%20some%20of%20the%20biggest%20issues%20facing%20the%20government.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A15%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fworld%2Flondon-calling-why-sunak-called-the-old-captain-back-to-the-crease%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Watch%20%7C%20The%20Modi%20Govt%20Is%20Guilty%20of%20%E2%80%98Killing%20the%20Constitution%20by%20a%201%2C000%20Cuts%E2%80%99%2C%20Says%20LSE%20Professor%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F13174732%2FKT-13-Nov-B.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20first%20Narendra%20Modi-led%20government%20(2014-2019)%20is%20guilty%20of%20%E2%80%9Ckilling%20the%20constitution%20by%20a%20thousand%20cuts%E2%80%9D%2C%20while%20the%20second%20Modi%20government%20has%20taken%20the%20process%20insidiously%20further%20in%20significant%20ways%2C%20says%20professor%20Tarunabh%20Khaitan%2C%20one%20of%20the%20foremost%20scholars%20of%20India%E2%80%99s%20constitution%20and%20its%20democracy.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EProfessor%20Khaitan%20said%20that%20many%20of%20India%E2%80%99s%20political%20parties%20and%20institutions%20have%20%E2%80%9Csleepwalked%20into%20(Modi%E2%80%99s)%20authoritarianism%E2%80%9D%20while%20others%20%E2%80%9Care%20complicit%E2%80%9D%20in%20Modi%E2%80%99s%20undermining%20of%20democracy.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20added%20that%20many%20people%20%E2%80%9Cdidn%E2%80%99t%20realise%20it%20was%20happening%E2%80%9D%20while%20%E2%80%9Chuge%20swathes%20of%20constitutional%20machinery%E2%80%9D%20were%20aware%20%5Bof%20it%5D%20but%20let%20it%20happen.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20a%2050-minute%20interview%20to%20Karan%20Thapar%20for%3Cem%3E%20The%20Wire%2C%3C%2Fem%3E%20Khaitan%2C%20who%20is%20professor%20of%20public%20law%20at%20the%20London%20School%20of%20Economics%2C%20presented%20an%20analytical%20framework%20for%20studying%20when%20a%20democracy%20is%20in%20peril.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20comprises%20three%20elements%20to%20do%20with%20how%20accountable%20is%20the%20executive.%20First%2C%20its%20accountability%20to%20the%20people.%20Second%2C%20its%20accountability%20to%20other%20state%20institutions%20like%20the%20opposition%20and%20the%20judiciary.%20Third%2C%20its%20accountability%20to%20the%20media%2C%20academic%20criticism%20and%20civil%20society%20institutions.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EProfessor%20Khaitan%20said%20this%20framework%20is%20%E2%80%9Cfair%20to%20the%20ruling%20party%20in%20power%E2%80%9D%20because%20it%20aims%20to%20distinguish%20policies%20in%20terms%20of%20their%20framework%20and%20not%20their%20ideology.%20In%20the%20interview%2C%20he%20discussed%20how%20the%20Modi%20government%20has%20failed%20to%20be%20accountable%20in%20each%20of%20the%20three%20respects%20that%20make%20up%20his%20analytical%20framework%2C%20i.e.%20to%20the%20people%2C%20to%20state%20institutions%20and%20to%20the%20media%20and%20civil%20society.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20argued%20that%20the%20first%20Modi%20government%E2%80%99s%20deliberate%20assault%20on%20democracy%20was%20corroborated%20and%20enhanced%20by%20the%20way%20%E2%80%9Cthe%20political%20opposition%20was%20constrained%2C%20especially%20by%20targeting%20the%20offices%20and%20institutions%20in%20which%20it%20still%20held%20sway%20(such%20as%20the%20upper%20chamber%20in%20the%20federal%20parliament%2C%20state%20governments%20it%20controlled%20and%20the%20office%20of%20the%20Leader%20of%20Opposition).%E2%80%9D%20He%20said%20it%20was%20also%20permitted%20by%20what%20he%20calls%20%E2%80%9Cdesign%20flaws%20in%20the%20constitution%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAsked%20how%20the%20Modi%20government%E2%80%99s%20assault%20on%20Indian%20democracy%20compares%20to%20Indira%20Gandhi%E2%80%99s%20Emergency%20of%201975%2C%20he%20said%20it%E2%80%99s%20less%20upfront%20and%20more%20insidious.%20It%20creates%20fear%2C%20which%20often%20leads%20to%20people%20self-censoring%20their%20actions.%20This%20applies%20particularly%20to%20the%20media.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESpeaking%20about%20the%20second%20Modi%20government%2C%20he%20spoke%20about%20its%20Hindutva%2FHindu%20Rashtra%20agenda.%20%E2%80%9CWe%E2%80%99re%20very%20close%20to%20Hindu%20Rashtra%20if%20it%20has%20not%20already%20been%20achieved%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELater%20in%20the%20interview%2C%20he%20added%3A%20%E2%80%9CHindu%20Rashtra%20is%20already%20here%20and%20only%20its%20formal%20announcement%20is%20awaited.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20him%2C%20the%20Modi%20government%E2%80%99s%20policy%20of%20Hindu%20Rashtra%20is%20not%20simply%20imperiling%20India%E2%80%99s%20democracy%20but%20%E2%80%9Credefining%20who%20we%20are%20as%20a%20people%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cdiv%3E%3Ciframe%20allowfullscreen%3D%5C%22allowfullscreen%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.youtube.com%2Fembed%2FsLRO4qs6Q-Q%3Fsi%3DfNsmFaA9IbXvgJwF%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22560%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22YouTube%20video%20player%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22315%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%20data-mce-type%3D%5C%22bookmark%5C%22%3E%EF%BB%BF%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fiframe%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1699878609000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F13174732%2FKT-13-Nov-B.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fvideo%2Fthe-modi-govt-is-guilty-of-killing-the-constitution-by-a-1000-cuts-says-lse-professor%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Professor%20Tarunabh%20Khaitan%20told%20Karan%20Thapar%20that%20many%20of%20India%E2%80%99s%20political%20parties%20and%20institutions%20have%20%E2%80%9Csleepwalked%20into%20(Modi%E2%80%99s)%20authoritarianism%E2%80%9D%20while%20others%20%E2%80%9Care%20complicit%E2%80%9D%20in%20Modi%E2%80%99s%20undermining%20of%20democracy.%C2%A0%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fvideo%2Fthe-modi-govt-is-guilty-of-killing-the-constitution-by-a-1000-cuts-says-lse-professor%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Retail%20inflation%20eases%20to%20four-month%20low%20of%204.87%25%20as%20food%20prices%20cool%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1699877957000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fbsmedia.business-standard.com%2F_media%2Fbs%2Fimg%2Farticle%2F2022-05%2F12%2Ffull%2F1652377939-7893.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Feconomy%2Fnews%2Fretail-inflation-eases-to-four-month-low-of-4-87-as-food-prices-cool-123111300755_1.html%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20government%20has%20tasked%20the%20RBI%20to%20ensure%20the%20CPI%20inflation%20remains%20at%204%20per%20cent%20with%20a%20margin%20of%202%20per%20cent%20on%20either%20side%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Feconomy%2Fnews%2Fretail-inflation-eases-to-four-month-low-of-4-87-as-food-prices-cool-123111300755_1.html%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww-business--standard-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Famp%2Feconomy%2Fnews%2Fretail-inflation-eases-to-four-month-low-of-4-87-as-food-prices-cool-123111300755_1.html%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Famp%2Feconomy%2Fnews%2Fretail-inflation-eases-to-four-month-low-of-4-87-as-food-prices-cool-123111300755_1.html%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22SC's%20Marriage%20Equality%20Judgment%3A%20Manufactured%20Classifications%20and%20Return%20of%20'Minuscule%20Minorities'%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F04%2F18112109%2FUntitled-design-16-2.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3ELast%20month%2C%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20delivered%20its%20judgment%20in%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmain.sci.gov.in%2Fsupremecourt%2F2022%2F36593%2F36593_2022_1_1501_47792_Judgement_17-Oct-2023.pdf%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3ESupriyo%20%40%20Supriya%20Chakraborty%20v.%20Union%20of%20India%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E.%20The%20court%E2%80%99s%20refusal%20to%20recognise%20same-sex%20marriage%2C%20I%20have%20argued%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Findconlawphil.wordpress.com%2F2023%2F10%2F21%2Fthe-supreme-courts-marriage-equality-judgment-i-on-the-right-to-marry-and-a-case-of-abstention-through-delegitimisation-guest-post%2F%5C%22%3Ehere%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20is%20best%20understood%20as%20the%20justification%20of%20institutional%20abstention%20through%20delegitimising%20the%20petitioners%E2%80%99%20case.%20This%20delegitimisation%2C%20I%20have%20argued%2C%20occurred%20through%20three%20means%3A%20the%20denial%20of%20the%20existence%20of%20a%20constitutional%20right%20to%20marry%3B%20a%20misidentification%20of%20the%20classification%E2%80%99s%20subject-matter%3B%20and%20the%20creation%20of%20artificial%20barriers%20in%20the%20court%E2%80%99s%20ability%20to%20transform%20social%20structures.%20I%20have%20covered%20the%20first%20of%20these%20means%20%E2%80%93%20the%20denial%20of%20the%20right%20to%20marry%20%E2%80%93%20in%20my%20previous%20post.%20The%20third%20means%2C%20which%20concerned%20the%20creation%20of%20artificial%20barriers%20to%20the%20court%E2%80%99s%20power%20to%20remedy%20rights%20violations%2C%20has%20been%20discussed%20by%20Hardik%20Choubey%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Findconlawphil.wordpress.com%2F2023%2F11%2F08%2Fthe-supreme-courts-marriage-equality-judgment-v-on-discrimination-judicial-remedies-and-judicial-abnegation-guest-post%2F%5C%22%3Ehere%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20this%20piece%2C%20I%20examine%20the%20second%20mode%20through%20which%20the%20court%20justified%20its%20institutional%20abstention%2C%20which%20concerned%20its%20response%20to%20the%20petitioners%E2%80%99%20claims%20under%20Article%2014.%20While%20the%20petitioners%20proposed%20that%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.indiacode.nic.in%2Fbitstream%2F123456789%2F15480%2F1%2Fspecial_marriage_act.pdf%5C%22%3ESpecial%20Marriage%20Act%2C%201954%3C%2Fa%3E%E2%80%99s%20(%E2%80%9CSMA%E2%80%9D)%20heteronormative%20conceptualisation%20of%20marriage%20caused%20the%20exclusion%20of%20persons%20who%20could%20not%20%E2%80%93%20due%20to%20ascriptive%20factors%20or%20otherwise%20%E2%80%93%20enter%20into%20such%20marriages%20and%20enjoy%20the%20bundle%20of%20rights%20they%20confer%2C%20the%20court%20rejected%20this%20claim%20at%20its%20very%20inception.%20It%20held%20that%20there%20was%2C%20in%20fact%2C%20no%20exclusion%20of%20non-heterosexual%20forms%20of%20marriage%20caused%20by%20the%20SMA%20because%20Parliament%20%E2%80%93%20let%20alone%20consciously%20excluding%20such%20marriage%20%E2%80%93%20was%20not%20even%20%3Cem%3Eaware%3C%2Fem%3E%20of%20its%20possible%20existence%20at%20the%20time%20of%20SMA%E2%80%99s%20enactment.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20approach%20towards%20identifying%20exclusion%20that%20prizes%20an%20%E2%80%9Cintent%20to%20exclude%E2%80%9D%20over%20factual%2C%20verifiable%20exclusion%2C%20I%20propose%2C%20is%20a%20novel%20and%20dangerous%20development%20in%20constitutional%20doctrine%2C%20and%20was%20designedly%20deployed%20to%20delegitimise%20the%20petitioners%E2%80%99%20Article%2014%20challenge.%20Further%2C%20I%20propose%20that%20Bhat%2C%20J.%2C%20in%20his%20Article%2014%20enquiry%2C%20commits%20a%20major%20misidentification%20of%20the%20classes%20the%20SMA%20creates%2C%20and%20creates%20diversions%20to%20circumvent%20a%20response%20to%20the%20SMA%E2%80%99s%20exclusion%20of%20non-heterosexual%20marriage.%20I%20make%20this%20argument%20in%20the%20following%20manner%20%E2%80%93%20%3Cem%3Efirst%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20I%20discuss%20the%20court%E2%80%99s%20Article%2014%20enquiry%20into%20the%20SMA%20and%20interrogate%20its%20major%20propositions%3B%20%3Cem%3Esecond%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20I%20propose%20that%20the%20court%20invents%20a%20novel%20standard%20of%20%E2%80%9Cintent%20to%20classify%E2%80%9D%20to%20determine%20a%20differentia%20under%20Article%2014%2C%20a%20dangerous%20development%20that%20risks%20a%20permanent%20entrenchment%20of%20regressive%20parliamentary%20actions%20based%20on%20a%20Court%E2%80%99s%20assessment%20of%20Parliament%E2%80%99s%20epistemic%20limitations%20at%20the%20moment%20of%20enactment%3B%20and%20%3Cem%3Ethird%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20I%20propose%20that%20the%20court%20substantially%20errs%20in%20identifying%20the%20classes%20the%20SMA%20creates%2C%20and%20circumvents%20a%20response%20to%20whether%20the%20SMA%E2%80%99s%20objective%20of%20regulating%20%3Cem%3Eexclusively%3C%2Fem%3E%20heterosexual%20marriage%20continues%20to%20remain%20legitimate.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EManipulating%20classifications%3A%20The%20court%E2%80%99s%20treatment%20of%20equality%20and%20non-discrimination%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20impugning%20SMA%E2%80%99s%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Findiankanoon.org%2Fdoc%2F594580%2F%5C%22%3ESection%204%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20the%20petitioners%20made%20a%20very%20straightforward%20argument%3A%20it%20provides%20a%20set%20of%20conjunctive%20conditions%20to%20be%20fulfilled%20by%20a%20couple%20seeking%20a%20marriage%2C%20with%20sub-section%20(c)%20mandating%20the%20existence%20of%20a%20%E2%80%9Cmale%E2%80%9D%20and%20a%20%E2%80%9Cfemale%E2%80%9D.%20This%20heteronormative%20prescription%20for%20marriage%20constitutes%20discrimination%20based%20on%20persons%E2%80%99%20sexual%20orientation.%20Sexual%20orientation%20is%20an%20ascriptive%20characteristic%20protected%20by%20Article%2015(1)%20of%20the%20Constitution%2C%20as%20interpreted%20by%20Chandrachud%2C%20J.%20(as%20he%20then%20was)%20in%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Findiankanoon.org%2Fdoc%2F168671544%2F%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3ENavtej%20Johar%20v.%20Union%20of%20India%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Without%20prejudice%20to%20the%20challenge%20based%20on%20Article%2015(1)%2C%20the%20impugned%20section%20also%20creates%20a%20classification%20between%20heterosexual%20and%20non-heterosexual%20couples%20for%20availing%20marriage%2C%20with%20such%20classification%20having%20no%20nexus%20with%20the%20SMA%E2%80%99s%20objective%20of%20providing%20a%20platform%20for%20the%20secular%20solemnization%20of%20marriages.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBhat%2C%20J.%2C%20speaking%20for%20the%20majority%2C%20follows%20the%20general%20tenor%20of%20delegitimization%20discernible%20in%20his%20treatment%20of%20the%20right%20to%20marry%2C%20making%20a%20similar%2C%20sweeping%20assertion%20here%20as%20well%3A%C2%A0he%20states%20that%20the%20SMA%2C%20instead%20of%20classifying%20between%20heterosexual%20and%20non-heterosexual%20couples%2C%20%3Cem%3Eactually%3C%2Fem%3E%20classifies%20between%20%E2%80%9Cheterosexual%20couples%20of%20differing%20faiths%E2%80%9D%20.%20This%20is%20because%20the%20exclusion%20of%20non-heterosexual%20couples%20from%20availing%20marriage%20was%20not%20a%20%3Cem%3Econscious%20parliamentary%20choice%3C%2Fem%3E%20made%20during%20SMA%E2%80%99s%20enactment%2C%20and%20was%2C%20instead%20caused%20by%20Parliament%E2%80%99s%20epistemic%20limits%3A%20it%20could%20not%20have%20known%20that%20marriage%20can%20be%20conceptualized%20in%20any%20manner%20but%20heteronormatively.%20He%20provides%20evidence%20of%20such%20epistemic%20limits%20in%20the%20form%20of%20Section%20377%20of%20the%20Indian%20Penal%20Code%2C%201860%20(%E2%80%9CIPC%E2%80%9D)%2C%20arguing%20that%20since%20even%20non-reproductive%20sexual%20intercourse%20constituted%20a%20penal%20offence%20at%20the%20time%20Parliament%20enacted%20the%20SMA%2C%20it%20could%20not%20have%20%3Cem%3Eimagined%3C%2Fem%3E%20the%20theoretical%20possibility%20of%20non-heterosexual%20marriage.%20On%20this%20basis%2C%20since%20Parliament%20could%20not%20have%20%3Cem%3Eintended%3C%2Fem%3E%20a%20classification%20%E2%80%93%20and%20the%20subsequent%20denial%20of%20marriage%20%E2%80%93%20based%20on%20sexual%20orientation%2C%20it%20cannot%20be%20said%20that%20the%20SMA%20%3Cem%3Ein%20fact%3C%2Fem%3E%20classified%20between%20heterosexual%20and%20non-heterosexual%20couples%20for%20availing%20marriage%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThere%20was%20no%20idea%20to%20exclude%20non-heterosexual%20couples%2C%20because%20at%20that%20time%2C%20even%20consensual%20physical%20intimacy%20of%20such%20persons%2C%20was%20outlawed%20by%20Section%20377%20IPC.%20So%2C%20while%20the%20Act%20sought%20to%20provide%20an%20avenue%20for%20those%20marriages%20that%20did%20not%20enjoy%20support%20in%20society%2C%20or%20did%20not%20have%20the%20benefit%20of%20custom%20to%20solemnise%2C%20it%20would%20be%20quite%20a%20stretch%20to%20say%20that%20this%20included%20same%20sex%20marriages.%20Therefore%2C%20the%20challenge%20to%20the%20constitutionality%20of%20the%20statute%2C%20must%20fail.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAnd%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cblockquote%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-quote%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%E2%80%A6The%20classification%20was%20primarily%20not%20between%20heterosexual%20and%20non-heterosexual%20couples%2C%20but%20heterosexual%20couples%20of%20differing%20faiths%E2%80%A6%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fblockquote%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20means%20that%20SMA%E2%80%99s%20differentia%20itself%20does%20not%20concern%20heterosexual%20and%20non-heterosexual%20couples%2C%20leading%20to%20a%20failure%20of%20the%20Article%2014%20challenge%20at%20its%20very%20first%20prong.%20Assuming%2C%20however%2C%20that%20the%20classification%20was%20based%20on%20sexual%20orientation%2C%20and%20was%20valid%20at%20the%20time%20it%20was%20made%20due%20to%20the%20existence%20of%20a%20rational%20nexus%20with%20its%20objective%20(of%20facilitating%20%3Cem%3Eonly%3C%2Fem%3E%20heterosexual%20inter-faith%20marriage)%2C%20the%20next%20question%20was%20whether%2C%20with%20the%20passage%20of%20time%2C%20this%20classification%20lost%20its%20nexus%20with%20the%20original%20objective%2C%20or%20the%20original%20objective%20itself%20turned%20illegitimate.%20This%20is%20because%20an%20Article%2014%20enquiry%20%E2%80%93%C2%A0apart%20from%20examining%20the%20classification%20and%20its%20nexus%20%E2%80%93%C2%A0also%20asks%20whether%20the%20objective%20pursued%20by%20the%20classification%20may%20be%20deemed%20%E2%80%9Clegitimate%E2%80%9D%20in%20the%20first%20place.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBhat%2C%20J.%2C%20in%20order%20to%20avoid%20answering%20this%20question%20genuinely%2C%20manoeuvres%20his%20way%20out%20of%20it%20through%20a%20very%20peculiar%20framing%20%E2%80%93%C2%A0instead%20of%20asking%20whether%20the%20objective%20of%20securing%20a%20platform%20for%20the%20solemnization%20of%20%3Cem%3Eonly%20%3C%2Fem%3Eheterosexual%20marriages%20(at%20the%20exclusion%20of%20non-heterosexual%20marriages)%20has%20turned%20illegitimate%2C%20he%20asks%20whether%20the%20objective%20of%20facilitating%20inter-faith%20heterosexual%20marriages%20can%20still%20%E2%80%93%20in%20today%E2%80%99s%20day%20and%20age%20%E2%80%93%20be%20deemed%20relevant.%20This%20question%2C%20though%20wholly%20disconnected%20from%20the%20question%20of%20the%20SMA%E2%80%99s%20validity%2C%20is%20answered%20in%20the%20affirmative%20to%20somehow%20sustain%20it%3A%20in%20other%20words%2C%20the%20continuing%20relevance%20of%20a%20platform%20to%20solemnize%20heterosexual%20inter-faith%20marriage%20was%20invoked%20to%20justify%20the%20exclusion%20of%20non-heterosexual%20marriage.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EChandrachud%2C%20CJ.%2C%20on%20the%20other%20hand%2C%20engages%20in%20no%20such%20intellectual%20gymnastics%2C%20holding%20straightforwardly%20that%20the%20Court%E2%80%99s%20incompetence%20to%20grant%20a%20suitable%20remedy%20for%20the%20SMA%E2%80%99s%20exclusion%20of%20non-heterosexual%20marriage%20renders%20an%20attempt%20at%20discerning%20its%20validity%20%E2%80%9Cfutile%E2%80%9D%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cblockquote%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-quote%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20in%20this%20case%2C%20an%20exercise%20to%20determine%20whether%20the%20SMA%20is%20unconstitutional%20because%20of%20under-inclusivity%20would%20be%20futile%20because%20of%20the%20limitations%20of%20this%20Court%E2%80%99s%20power%20to%20grant%20a%20remedy.%20Whether%20a%20change%20should%20be%20brought%20into%20the%20legislative%20regime%20of%20the%20SMA%20is%20for%20Parliament%20to%20determine.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fblockquote%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThus%2C%20based%20on%20his%20assessment%20of%20the%20degree%20of%20judicial%20intervention%20necessary%20to%20effectuate%20non-heterosexual%20marriage%2C%20he%20prefers%20abstention%20as%20the%20best%20option.%20Kaul%2C%20J.%2C%20who%20concurs%20with%20Chandrachud%2C%20CJ.%2C%20does%20choose%20to%20answer%20this%20%E2%80%9Cfutile%E2%80%9D%20question%2C%20holding%20that%20the%20exclusion%20of%20non-heterosexual%20marriage%20u%2Fs%20the%204%20of%20the%20SMA%20does%2C%20in%20fact%2C%20constitute%20a%20violation%20of%20Article%2014%20.%20He%20registers%20his%20disagreement%20with%20Bhat%2C%20J.%2C%20noting%20that%20his%20assessment%20of%20the%20legislative%20objective%2C%20such%20that%20the%20SMA%20aimed%20to%20provide%20a%20platform%20for%20the%20solemnization%20of%20%3Cem%3Eonly%3C%2Fem%3E%20heterosexual%20marriages%2C%20constituted%20a%20conflation%20of%20the%20classification%20and%20its%20objective%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cblockquote%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-quote%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3EI%20respectfully%20disagree%20with%20my%20brother%20Justice%20Ravindra%20Bhat%2C%20that%20the%20sole%20intention%20of%20the%20SMA%20was%20to%20enable%20marriage%20of%20heterosexual%20couples%20exclusively.%20To%20my%20mind%2C%20the%20stated%20objective%20of%20the%20SMA%20was%20not%20to%20regulate%20marriages%20on%20the%20basis%20of%20sexual%20orientation.%20This%20cannot%20be%20so%20as%20it%20would%20amount%20to%20conflating%20the%20differentia%20with%20the%20object%20of%20the%20statute.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fblockquote%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20other%20words%2C%20the%20fact%20that%20the%20SMA%20%3Cem%3Epresently%3C%2Fem%3E%20regulates%20heterosexual%20marriages%20exclusively%20provides%20no%20hint%20to%20its%20legislative%20objective%2C%20for%20%E2%80%9Cwe%E2%80%A6act%20in%20ways%20that%20do%20not%E2%80%A6correspond%20to%20our%20intent%E2%80%9D.%20Further%2C%20assuming%20Bhat%2C%20J.%E2%80%99s%20identification%20of%20SMA%E2%80%99s%20objective%20as%20the%20exclusive%20regulation%20of%20inter-faith%20marriage%20to%20be%20correct%2C%20he%20notes%20that%20this%20objective%20diverged%20with%20the%20classification%2C%20and%20was%20not%20subserved%20by%20the%20exclusion%20of%20non-heterosexual%20marriage.%20The%20final%20leg%20of%20his%20disagreement%20with%20Bhat%2C%20J.%20concerns%20the%20latter%E2%80%99s%20formalistic%20affirmation%20of%20the%20SMA%E2%80%99s%20constitutionality%20based%20only%20on%20intelligible%20differentia%20and%20rational%20nexus%2C%20without%20an%20enquiry%20into%20the%20constitutionality%20of%20the%20%3Cem%3Eobjective%3C%2Fem%3E%20of%20exclusively%20regulating%20heterosexual%20marriage.%20The%20objective%20of%20the%20sole%20regulation%20of%20heterosexual%20marriage%2C%20Kaul%2C%20J.%20notes%2C%20must%20be%20a%20%3Cem%3Ecause%3C%2Fem%3E%20of%20the%20SMA%E2%80%99s%20unconstitutionality%2C%20instead%20of%20a%20%3Cem%3Ejustification%3C%2Fem%3E%20to%20sustain%20its%20validity.%20This%20is%20because%20exclusion%20based%20on%20sexual%20orientation%20%E2%80%93%20akin%20to%20discrimination%20based%20on%20%E2%80%9Csex%E2%80%9D%20%E2%80%93%20is%20prohibited%20under%20Article%2015(1)%2C%20and%20cannot%20constitute%20a%20legitimate%20state%20objective.%20Ultimately%2C%20however%2C%20even%20Kaul%20J.%20notes%20that%20a%20%E2%80%9Cspider%E2%80%99s%20web%E2%80%9D%20of%20legislation%20would%20be%20disrupted%20if%20the%20Court%20tinkers%20with%20the%20SMA%2C%20and%20the%20consideration%20of%20separation%20of%20powers%20trumps%20that%20of%20rights-violation.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDespite%20the%20disagreements%20expressed%20in%20Kaul%2C%20J.%E2%80%99s%20dissent%2C%20the%20following%20propositions%20emerge%20from%20the%20majority%20opinion%3A%20%3Cem%3Efirst%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20the%20%E2%80%9Cintent%20to%20classify%E2%80%9D%20%E2%80%93%C2%A0which%20can%20be%20discerned%20from%20a%20study%20of%20Parliament%E2%80%99s%20imaginative%20limitations%20at%20the%20moment%20of%20enactment%20%E2%80%93%C2%A0is%20a%20factor%20in%20determining%20a%20classification%E2%80%99s%20subject-matter%3B%20%3Cem%3Esecond%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20a%20classification%20may%20not%20express%20a%20relationship%20between%20an%20included%20and%20excluded%20group%2C%20and%20can%2C%20instead%2C%20be%20defined%20in%20reference%20only%20to%20the%20included%20group%3B%20and%20%3Cem%3Ethird%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20a%20classification%E2%80%99s%20pursuit%20of%20a%20constitutionally%20incompatible%20(and%20morally%20repugnant)%20objective%20is%20acceptable%2C%20and%20can%20be%20invoked%20to%20sustain%20its%20validity.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EOn%20the%20regressive%20invention%20of%20the%20%E2%80%9Cintent%20to%20classify%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20classification%2C%20as%20is%20traditionally%20understood%2C%20concerns%20the%20creation%20of%20real%20and%20tangible%20groups%2C%20on%20whom%20different%20legal%20standards%20apply.%20It%20arises%20in%20multiple%20ways%20%E2%80%93%20a%20distinct%20legal%20regime%20may%20be%20created%20to%20govern%20a%20group%20exclusively%20(this%20includes%20all%20kinds%20of%20codified%20personal%20law%2C%20such%20as%20the%20Hindu%20Marriage%20Act%2C%201955%3B%20specific%20provisions%20may%20be%20created%20to%20determine%20a%20group%E2%80%99s%20rights%20Section%20118%20of%20the%20Indian%20Succession%20Act%2C%201925%3B%20or%20restrictions%20may%20be%20levied%20on%20groups%E2%80%99%20exercise%20of%20their%20pre-existing%20rights%20Section%2016%20of%20the%20Orissa%20Municipal%20Act%2C%201950.%20A%20classification%2C%20in%20terms%20of%20distinguishing%20between%20groups%20to%20whom%20distinct%20legal%20standards%20apply%2C%20need%20not%20be%20made%20legislatively%20explicit%2C%20and%20can%20arise%20as%20a%20natural%20corollary%20to%20the%20inclusion%20of%20a%20single%20group.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20identification%20of%20a%20differentia%20is%20a%20largely%20objective%20enquiry%2C%20and%20requires%20the%20demonstration%20of%20concrete%20groups%20being%20created%20through%20legislation.%20In%20%3Cem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Findiankanoon.org%2Fdoc%2F845216%2F%5C%22%3EAnuj%20Garg%20v.%20Hotel%20Association%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%3C%2Fem%3E%20for%20example%2C%20Section%2030%20of%20the%20Punjab%20Excise%20Act%2C%201914%20%E2%80%93%C2%A0which%20prohibited%20women%20from%20being%20employed%20by%20establishments%20serving%20liquor%20%E2%80%93%20was%20challenged%20under%20Articles%2014%20and%2015.%20In%20case%20the%20Court%20employed%20%3Cem%3ESupriyo%E2%80%99s%3C%2Fem%3E%20logic%20of%20%E2%80%9Cintent%20to%20classify%E2%80%9D%2C%20it%20could%20have%20held%20that%20at%20the%20time%20of%20enactment%2C%20Parliament%20could%20never%20have%20envisioned%20the%20possibility%20of%20women%20working%20in%20liquor%20establishments%2C%20and%20never%20intended%20to%20consciously%20exclude%20them%20from%20such%20employment%2C%20which%20in%20turn%20meant%20that%20Section%2030%20did%20not%20classify%20between%20%E2%80%9Cmen%E2%80%9D%20and%20%E2%80%9Cwomen%E2%80%9D.%20It%2C%20however%2C%20did%20not%20choose%20this%20path%2C%20noting%20straightforwardly%20the%20existence%20of%20such%20classification%2C%20enquiring%20next%20into%20its%20constitutional%20compatibility.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20use%20of%20the%20%E2%80%9Cintent%20to%20classify%E2%80%9D%20principle%2C%20when%20applied%20to%20other%20cases%2C%20would%20have%20similarly%20regressive%20consequences%2C%20causing%20a%20permanent%20entrenchment%20of%20the%20status%20quo%20by%20justifying%20it%20using%20lawmakers%E2%80%99%20intellectual%20limitations%20to%20conceptualize%20a%20fairer%2C%20equal%20world%20at%20the%20time%20of%20enactment.%C2%A0In%20%3Cem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Findiankanoon.org%2Fdoc%2F1241462%2F%5C%22%3EGitha%20Hariharan%20v.%20RBI%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%3C%2Fem%3E%20the%20Court%20could%20have%20noted%20that%20Parliament%2C%20at%20the%20time%20of%20enacting%20the%20Hindu%20Minority%20and%20Guardianship%20Act%2C%201956%2C%20could%20never%20have%20known%20that%20women%20could%20be%20equal%20guardians%20of%20minors%2C%20and%20no%20classification%20between%20%E2%80%9Cmen%E2%80%9D%20and%20%E2%80%9Cwomen%E2%80%9D%20lay%20in%20the%20subordination%20of%20women%E2%80%99s%20rights%20to%20guardianship%3B%20in%20%3Cem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Findiankanoon.org%2Fdoc%2F1216671%2F%5C%22%3EMadhu%20Kishwar%20v.%20State%20of%20Bihar%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20it%20could%20have%20wholly%20rejected%20tribal%20women%E2%80%99s%20demands%20for%20equal%20succession%20rights%20on%20the%20ground%20that%20the%20Legislative%20Assembly%20%E2%80%93%20when%20undertaking%20the%20codification%20of%20customs%20%E2%80%93%20could%20not%20have%20envisioned%20a%20constitutionally-compliant%2C%20gender-equal%20process%20thereof%3B%20and%20in%20%3Cem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Findiankanoon.org%2Fdoc%2F715470%2F%5C%22%3EVasantha%20R%20v.%20Union%20of%20India%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20it%20could%20have%20upheld%20Section%2066(1)(b)%20of%20the%20Factories%20Act%2C%201948%20on%20the%20ground%20that%20Parliament%20could%20not%20have%20envisioned%20that%20women%20may%20also%20work%20during%20night%20hours%2C%20making%20their%20exclusion%20an%20unintentional%20incidence%20of%20well-meaning%20legislation.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMy%20point%2C%20therefore%2C%20is%20that%20any%20standard%20enquiring%20into%20an%20%E2%80%9Cintent%20to%20classify%E2%80%9D%20for%20determining%20a%20law%E2%80%99s%20differentia%20is%20bound%20to%20whitewash%20highly%20regressive%2C%20hostile%20acts%20of%20discrimination%20through%20a%20simple%20denial%20of%20the%20classification%E2%80%99s%20existence%2C%20the%20only%20evidence%20for%20which%20a%20Court%20may%20offer%20is%20Parliament%E2%80%99s%20epistemic%20limits%2C%20along%20with%20its%20inability%20to%20conceptualize%20an%20equal%20society%20at%20the%20time%20it%20enacted%20the%20relevant%20law.%20Such%20an%20enquiry%2C%20apart%20from%20being%20generally%20historically%20inaccurate%20by%20presuming%20the%20state%20of%20mind%20of%20hundreds%20of%20parliamentarians%20sitting%20in%20the%201950s%2C%20has%20the%20effect%20of%20legitimizing%20present-day%20discrimination%20on%20the%20ground%20that%20past%20parliamentarians%20could%20%3Cem%3Enever%20have%20thought%3C%2Fem%3E%20that%20such%20groups%20possessed%20the%20basic%20minimum%20dignity%20to%20be%20%E2%80%9Ckept%20in%20mind%E2%80%9D%20while%20being%20excluded!%20In%20other%20words%2C%20such%20groups%20were%20so%20unimportant%20%E2%80%93%C2%A0constituting%2C%20perhaps%2C%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Findiankanoon.org%2Fdoc%2F58730926%2F%5C%22%3E%E2%80%9Cminuscule%20minority%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%93%C2%A0that%20even%20their%20exclusion%20was%20a%20by-product%20of%20things%20running%20their%20natural%20course.%20Bhat%2C%20J.%E2%80%99s%20reliance%20on%20Section%20377%20of%20the%20IPC%20to%20justify%20the%20exclusion%20of%20non-heterosexual%20marriage%2C%20read%20in%20this%20light%2C%20is%20highly%20disturbing%3A%20it%20indicates%20that%20past%20unconstitutionality%20serves%20as%20a%20justification%20for%20present%20discrimination%2C%20for%20such%20unconstitutionality%20was%20the%20%3Cem%3Enorm%3C%2Fem%3E%20to%20be%20adhered%20to%20by%20Parliament.%20Further%2C%20in%20case%20this%20logic%20were%20to%20be%20applied%20in%20%3Cem%3ENavtej%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20even%20Section%20377%20would%20have%20likely%20succeeded%20in%20the%20Article%2014%20challenge%2C%20for%20in%201860%2C%20the%20Imperial%20Legislative%20Council%20%E2%80%93%20with%20its%20intellectual%20and%20moral%20limitations%2C%20along%20with%20its%20adherence%20to%20English%20law%20criminalizing%20homosexuality%20%E2%80%93%C2%A0could%20not%20have%20known%20that%20sexual%20intercourse%20in%20non-heterosexual%20relationships%20is%20a%20facet%20of%20human%20dignity%20and%20individual%20autonomy.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELastly%2C%20it%20is%20unclear%20as%20to%20how%20Parliament%E2%80%99s%20reliance%20on%20an%20unconstitutional%20provision%20justifies%20its%20choice%20to%20further%20discriminate%2C%20for%20a%20declaration%20of%20unconstitutionality%20has%20effect%20of%20making%20a%20law%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmain.sci.gov.in%2Fsupremecourt%2F2007%2F415%2F415_2007_2_1501_46897_Judgement_11-Sep-2023.pdf%5C%22%3E%E2%80%9Cvoid%20ab%20initio%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20meaning%20invalidity%20that%20attaches%20from%20the%20moment%20of%20enactment.%20Section%20377%20was%20invalid%2C%20therefore%2C%20at%20least%20since%20the%20coming%20into%20force%20of%20the%20Constitution%2C%20in%201950.%20Judicial%20invocation%20of%20parliamentary%20reliance%20on%20invalid%20law%2C%20in%20order%20to%20justify%20Parliament%E2%80%99s%20myopic%20imagination%20of%20marriage%20in%20the%20past%2C%20thus%20stands%20in%20murky%20territory.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20this%20basis%2C%20I%20submit%20that%20the%20implications%20of%20a%20doctrinal%20adoption%20of%20an%20%E2%80%9Cintent%20to%20classify%E2%80%9D%20to%20determine%20differentia%20are%20highly%20disastrous%2C%20and%20are%20likely%20to%20stultify%20equality%20jurisprudence%20by%20perpetually%20pointing%20to%20a%20regressive%20past.%20The%20only%20way%20such%20stultification%20can%20be%20prevented%2C%20however%2C%20is%20to%20face%20reality%20and%20confront%20factual%2C%20verifiable%20exclusion%2C%20instead%20of%20ruminating%20over%20parliamentarians%E2%80%99%20state%20of%20mind%20in%20the%201950s.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E%E2%80%9CClassifying%20without%20classification%E2%80%9D%20and%20no-holds-barred%20objectives%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EI%20now%20address%20the%20remaining%20two%20prongs%20of%20Bhat%2C%20J.%E2%80%99s%20arguments%20%E2%80%93%20%3Cem%3Efirst%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20that%20the%20SMA%20actually%20makes%20a%20classification%20involving%20%E2%80%9Cheterosexual%20couples%20of%20differing%20faiths%E2%80%9D%3B%20and%20%3Cem%3Esecond%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20that%20since%20the%20SMA%20serves%20the%20legitimate%20objective%20of%20providing%20a%20platform%20to%20solemnize%20inter-faith%20marriages%2C%20a%20challenge%20to%20its%20validity%20is%20obviated.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20the%20first%20prong%2C%20it%20is%20submitted%20that%20Bhat%2C%20J.%E2%80%99s%20identification%20of%20the%20classification%20u%2Fs%204%20as%20comprising%20%E2%80%9Cheterosexual%20couples%20of%20differing%20faiths%E2%80%9D%2C%20instead%20of%20one%20between%20%E2%80%9Cnon-heterosexual%20inter-faith%20couples%E2%80%9D%20and%20%E2%80%9Cheterosexual%20inter-faith%20couples%E2%80%9D%2C%20constitutes%20a%20complete%20misidentification.%20A%20differentia%2C%20as%20discussed%20above%2C%20must%20comprise%20two%20groups%20%E2%80%93%20one%20included%2C%20and%20another%20excluded.%20In%20stating%20that%20the%20classification%20involves%20only%20%E2%80%9Cheterosexual%20couples%20of%20differing%20faiths%E2%80%9D%2C%20there%20is%20no%20clarity%20of%20the%20group%20being%20excluded%20at%20the%20cost%20of%20this%20group%E2%80%99s%20inclusion%2C%20apart%20from%20non-heterosexual%20inter-faith%20couples%20%E2%80%93%C2%A0who%20Bhat%2C%20J.%20has%20already%20concluded%2C%20are%20not%20being%20excluded%20by%20the%20SMA.%20One%20argument%20to%20sustain%20his%20identification%20of%20the%20included%20group%2C%20however%2C%20could%20have%20identified%20the%20excluded%20group%20as%20%E2%80%9Cheterosexual%20couples%20of%20the%20same%20faith%E2%80%9D.%20This%20identification%2C%20however%2C%20would%20also%20be%20erroneous%2C%20for%20the%20SMA%20does%20not%20prohibit%20a%20couple%2C%20both%20whose%20members%20practise%20the%20same%20faith%2C%20from%20solemnizing%20a%20marriage%20thereunder.%20The%20SMA%2C%20apart%20from%20containing%20no%20same-faith%20prohibition%2C%20specifically%20envisions%20couples%20marrying%20thereunder%20%E2%80%93%20both%20whose%20members%20are%20Hindu%20%E2%80%93%C2%A0u%2Fs%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Findiankanoon.org%2Fdoc%2F11410%2F%5C%22%3E21A%3C%2Fa%3E.%20There%20cannot%2C%20fundamentally%2C%20be%20a%20classification%20involving%20a%20single%20group%20by%20itself%2C%20making%20Bhat%2C%20J.%E2%80%99s%20identification%20of%20the%20classification%20incorrect.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20the%20second%20prong%2C%20I%20propose%20that%20the%20Court%E2%80%99s%20reliance%20on%20the%20objective%20of%20creating%20a%20platform%20for%20solemnizing%20heterosexual%20inter-faith%20marriages%2C%20in%20order%20to%20sustain%20the%20SMA%E2%80%99s%20validity%2C%20whitewashes%20the%20issue%20of%20exclusion.%20To%20recap%2C%20the%20Court%20framed%20the%20question%20as%20to%20whether%20the%20SMA%E2%80%99s%20%3Cem%3Eoriginal%3C%2Fem%3E%20objective%20%E2%80%93%20which%20was%20to%20facilitate%20heterosexual%20inter-faith%20marriages%20%E2%80%93%20has%20turned%20illegitimate%20with%20the%20passage%20of%20time.%20In%20response%2C%20the%20Court%20states%20that%20this%20objective%20is%20as%20relevant%20today%20as%20it%20was%20at%20the%20time%20the%20SMA%20was%20enacted%2C%20for%20persons%20seek%20to%20marry%20persons%20of%20different%20faiths%20regularly%20nowadays.%20Bhat%2C%20J.%20also%20remarks%20that%20the%20SMA%20cannot%20be%20deemed%20wholly%20meaningless%20due%20to%20its%20exclusion%20of%20non-heterosexual%20marriages%2C%20for%20its%20relevance%20%E2%80%93%20insofar%20as%20it%20concerns%20heterosexual%20marriages%20%E2%80%93%20is%20alive%20and%20well%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cblockquote%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-quote%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%E2%80%A6The%20relevance%20of%20SMA%20has%20gained%20more%20ground%2C%20because%20of%20increasing%20awareness%20and%20increasing%20exercise%20of%20choice%20by%20intending%20spouses%20belonging%20to%20different%20faiths%E2%80%A6It%20cannot%20be%20said%2C%20by%20any%20stretch%20of%20the%20imagination%20that%20the%20exclusion%20of%20non-heterosexual%20couples%20from%20the%20fold%20of%20SMA%20has%20resulted%20in%20its%20ceasing%20to%20have%20any%20rationale%2C%20and%20thus%20becoming%20discriminatory%20in%20operation.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fblockquote%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%2C%20however%2C%20was%20uncontested%2C%20for%20none%20argued%20the%20SMA%E2%80%99s%20loss%20of%20legitimacy%20based%20on%20the%20objective%20of%20facilitating%20inter-faith%20marriages%20going%20stale.%20The%20argument%20concerned%20the%20invalidity%20of%20the%20SMA%E2%80%99s%20objective%20of%20regulating%20%3Cem%3Eexclusively%3C%2Fem%3E%20heterosexual%20marriage%2C%20which%20caused%20the%20exclusion%20of%20all%20other%20forms.%20An%20assessment%20of%20the%20constitutional%20compatibility%20of%20this%20objective%2C%20however%2C%20is%20not%20done%20in%20Bhat%2C%20J.%E2%80%99s%20opinion%2C%20for%20he%20undertakes%20a%20repetitive%20diversion%20to%20the%20SMA%E2%80%99s%20continued%20relevance%20of%20facilitating%20inter-faith%20marriage%2C%20portraying%20the%20latter%20as%20demonstrative%20of%20the%20SMA%E2%80%99s%20commendable%20virtues.%20Such%20virtues%20in%20one%20respect%2C%20however%2C%20are%20no%20justification%20for%20exclusion%20in%20another%20%E2%80%93%C2%A0and%20it%20was%20an%20enquiry%20into%20the%20latter%20that%20was%20Bhat%2C%20J.%E2%80%99s%20prerogative%20after%20identifying%20the%20SMA%E2%80%99s%20objective%20as%20regulating%20exclusively%20heterosexual%20inter-faith%20marriage.%20This%20he%20did%20not%20undertake.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EKaul%2C%20J.%E2%80%99s%20dissent%20points%20tersely%20to%20such%20errors%3A%20he%20notes%20that%20since%20an%20objective%20must%20be%20constitutionally%20compliant%2C%20an%20objective%20of%20catering%20exclusively%20to%20heterosexual%20couples%20violates%20Article%2015(1)%2C%20and%20Bhat%2C%20J.%E2%80%99s%20invocation%20thereof%20to%20justify%20the%20classification%20was%2C%20therefore%2C%20wrong.%20Apart%20from%20the%20dissent%2C%20it%20must%20be%20noted%20that%20Bhat%2C%20J.%20sets%20the%20considerations%20of%20inter-faith%20marriage%20and%20non-heterosexual%20marriage%20at%20opposing%20ends%2C%20portraying%20the%20petitioners%20as%20attempting%20to%20undo%20the%20SMA%E2%80%99s%20prized%20progressive%20credentials.%20This%2C%20however%2C%20was%20not%20the%20case%3A%20the%20petitioners%20consistently%20pointed%20to%20the%20necessity%20of%20preserving%20the%20SMA%E2%80%99s%20inter-faith%20marriage%20solemnization%20machinery%2C%20which%20in%20turn%20made%20a%20%E2%80%9Creading%20down%E2%80%9D%20of%20the%20SMA%20to%20permit%20non-heterosexual%20marriage%20the%20preferable%20relief%2C%20instead%20of%20a%20declaration%20of%20its%20unconstitutionality%20(%3Cem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.livelaw.in%2Fpdf_upload%2Fwritten-submissions-in-utkarsh-saxena-v-uoi-469115.pdf%5C%22%3EDr.%20Abhishek%20Singhvi%E2%80%99s%20Written%20Submissions%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fem%3E).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EConclusion%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20this%20basis%2C%20I%20submit%20that%20the%20instant%20case%20invokes%20a%20mix%20of%20novel%20constitutional%20doctrine%2C%20erroneous%20class-identification%2C%20and%20deliberate%20diversions%20to%20reject%20the%20petitioners%E2%80%99%20Article%2014%20case.%20The%20most%20dangerous%20development%20of%20the%20judgment%2C%20which%20is%20susceptible%20to%20immense%20misuse%2C%20concerns%20the%20invention%20of%20an%20%E2%80%9Cintent%20to%20classify%E2%80%9D%20standard%2C%20pursuant%20to%20which%20a%20court%20may%20deny%20the%20existence%20of%20factual%2C%20real%20classes%20by%20pointing%20to%20imaginative%20limitations%20to%20envision%20an%20equal%20world%20at%20the%20time%20of%20enactment.%20The%20court%2C%20in%20effect%2C%20states%20that%20non-heterosexual%20persons%20possessed%20no%20dignity%20to%20even%20be%20%3Cem%3Ethought%20of%3C%2Fem%3E%20to%20be%20excluded%20from%20marriage%2C%20and%20are%2C%20therefore%2C%20not%20the%20subject%20of%20SMA%E2%80%99s%20classification.%20The%20subsequent%20class-misidentification%2C%20along%20with%20portraying%20as%20legitimate%20the%20regulation%20of%20exclusively%20heterosexual%20marriage%2C%20adds%20insult%20to%20injury%2C%20and%20marks%20a%20substantial%20setback%20to%20Indian%20equality%20jurisprudence.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1699876847000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F04%2F18112109%2FUntitled-design-16-2.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fscs-marriage-equality-judgment-manufactured-classifications-and-return-of-minuscule-minorities%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20court's%20assertion%20that%20the%20Special%20Marriage%20Act%2C%201954%20didn't%20exclude%20non-heterosexual%20marriages%2C%20attributing%20it%20to%20Parliament's%20lack%20of%20awareness%20during%20enactment%2C%20is%20a%20novel%20and%20dangerous%20constitutional%20doctrine%2C%20potentially%20legitimising%20regressive%20laws%20based%20on%20historical%20intellectual%20limitations.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A3%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fscs-marriage-equality-judgment-manufactured-classifications-and-return-of-minuscule-minorities%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Iceland%20volcano%3A%20How%20big%20could%20eruption%20be%20and%20will%20it%20produce%20another%20huge%20ash%20cloud%3F%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1699876020000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fe3.365dm.com%2F23%2F11%2F768x432%2Fskynews-iceland-volcano_6358946.jpg%3F20231113133934%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews.sky.com%2Fstory%2Ficeland-volcano-how-big-could-eruption-be-and-will-it-produce-another-huge-ash-cloud-13007252%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Iceland%20is%20bracing%20for%20a%20volcanic%20eruption%20in%20the%20coming%20days%20after%20a%20series%20of%20earthquakes%20and%20evidence%20of%20hot%20magma%20flowing%20quickly%20underground.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A700%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews.sky.com%2Fstory%2Ficeland-volcano-how-big-could-eruption-be-and-will-it-produce-another-huge-ash-cloud-13007252%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews-sky-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fnews.sky.com%2Fstory%2Famp%2Ficeland-volcano-how-big-could-eruption-be-and-will-it-produce-another-huge-ash-cloud-13007252%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews.sky.com%2Fstory%2Famp%2Ficeland-volcano-how-big-could-eruption-be-and-will-it-produce-another-huge-ash-cloud-13007252%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Ex-NFL%20player%20among%20six%20people%20killed%20in%20car%20crash%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1699875060000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fe3.365dm.com%2F23%2F11%2F768x432%2Fskynews-houston-dj-hayden_6359192.jpg%3F20231113155204%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews.sky.com%2Fstory%2Fd-j-hayden-ex-nfl-player-among-six-people-killed-in-houston-car-crash-13007230%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22A%20former%20American%20football%20player%20has%20been%20killed%20in%20a%20car%20crash%20in%20Houston.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A191%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews.sky.com%2Fstory%2Fd-j-hayden-ex-nfl-player-among-six-people-killed-in-houston-car-crash-13007230%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews-sky-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fnews.sky.com%2Fstory%2Famp%2Fd-j-hayden-ex-nfl-player-among-six-people-killed-in-houston-car-crash-13007230%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews.sky.com%2Fstory%2Famp%2Fd-j-hayden-ex-nfl-player-among-six-people-killed-in-houston-car-crash-13007230%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22The%20Killer%3A%20The%20Clinical%20Assassin%20in%20a%20Film%20Made%20by%20a%20Clinical%20Director%20David%20Fincher%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F13161217%2Fimage-1495.png%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3EEarly%20on%20in%20David%20Fincher%E2%80%99s%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Killer%3C%2Fem%3E%20%E2%80%93%20the%20unnamed%20titular%20character%20(Michael%20Fassbender)%20says%20%E2%80%98scepticism%20is%20often%20mistaken%20for%20cynicism%E2%80%99.%20It%E2%80%99s%20something%20that%20could%20be%20said%20for%20the%20director%20too.%20Fincher%2C%20famous%20for%20his%20clinical%20approach%20while%20showing%20human%20beings%20at%20their%20most%20depraved%2C%20has%20often%20been%20described%20as%20a%20cynic.%20He%E2%80%99s%20maintained%20that%20the%20core%20philosophy%20of%20his%20films%20is%3A%20people%20are%20perverts.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20if%20one%20delves%20deeper%20into%20his%20work%2C%20it%E2%80%99s%20not%20hard%20to%20find%20that%20Fincher%20is%20a%20sceptic%2C%20not%20a%20cynic%2C%20the%20difference%20being%20he%20doesn%E2%80%99t%20automatically%20assume%20the%20worst%20of%20human%20beings.%20He%20probably%20wants%20to%20believe%20in%20goodness%2C%20but%20there%20are%20just%20too%20many%20examples%20in%20the%20world%20to%20plant%20a%20seed%20of%20permanent%20doubt.%20The%20protagonist%20in%20Fincher%E2%80%99s%20latest%20might%20constantly%20remind%20himself%20that%20%E2%80%98empathy%20is%20a%20weakness%E2%80%99%2C%20but%20he%20shows%20himself%20to%20be%20not%20cold-blooded%20on%20more%20than%20one%20occasion%20in%20the%20film.%20Despite%20whatever%20he%20might%20think%20of%20himself%2C%20he%20manages%20to%20find%20his%20moral%20centre%20to%20do%20the%20fair%20thing%2C%20even%20in%20the%20most%20unfair%20circumstances.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20plot%20in%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Killer%3C%2Fem%3E%20is%20painfully%20simple%3A%20A%20hitman%20botches%20up%20a%20job%2C%20and%20he%20goes%20on%20the%20run.%20Returning%20home%20to%20the%20Dominican%20Republic%2C%20he%20realises%20his%20employer%20has%20hurt%20his%20long-time%20partner%2C%20in%20an%20attempt%20to%20learn%20about%20his%20whereabouts.%20The%20protagonist%2C%20who%20never%20acts%20out%20of%20emotion%20%E2%80%93%20all%20his%20actions%20are%20measured%2C%20he%20blends%20into%20the%20crowd%20like%20sugar%20in%20hot%20milk%20%E2%80%93%20breaks%20his%20rules%20for%20love.%20He%20seeks%20out%20his%20handler%20Hodges%20%5BCharles%20Parnell%5D%2C%20the%20assassins%20sent%20to%20torture%20his%20partner%2C%20and%20the%20client%20%E2%80%93%20a%20billionaire.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEven%20though%20the%20plot%20in%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Killer%3C%2Fem%3E%20seems%20direct%2C%20it%20won%E2%80%99t%20be%20far-fetched%20to%20think%20that%20the%20film%20could%20present%20itself%20as%20a%20metaphor%20for%20the%20director%E2%80%99s%20tempestuous%20relationship%20with%20the%20studios%20over%20his%20three-decade%20career.%20Just%20look%20out%20for%20the%20caption%20on%20the%20film%E2%80%99s%20poster%3A%20execution%20is%20everything.%20Those%20are%20words%20for%20a%20filmmaker%20to%20die%20by.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFincher%E2%80%99s%20run-ins%20with%20the%20Hollywood%20system%20have%20been%20the%20stuff%20of%20legends%2C%20especially%20the%20way%20he%20began%20his%20career%20with%20the%20troubled%20production%20of%20%3Cem%3EAlien%203%3C%2Fem%3E%20(1992).%20After%20his%20adaptation%20of%20Steig%20Larsson%E2%80%99s%20%3Cem%3EMillennium%3C%2Fem%3E%20trilogy%20was%20shut%20down%20following%20just%20one%20film%2C%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Girl%20with%20The%20Dragon%20Tattoo%3C%2Fem%3E%20(2011)%2C%20and%20the%20show%20%3Cem%3EMindhunter%3C%2Fem%3E%20(2017-2019)%20was%20discontinued%20after%20two%20seasons%20for%20being%20%E2%80%98too%20expensive%E2%80%99%20for%20the%20numbers%20it%20ended%20up%20drawing%2C%20one%20can%20almost%20sense%20the%20weariness%20in%20the%2061-year-old%20filmmaker.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHis%20previous%20film%2C%20%3Cem%3EMank%3C%2Fem%3E%20(2021)%2C%20a%20black-and-white%2C%20no-questions-asked%20passion%20project%2C%20based%20on%20a%20screenplay%20written%20by%20his%20father%20(Jack%20Fincher)%20on%20the%20making%20of%20%3Cem%3ECitizen%20Kane%20%3C%2Fem%3E(1931)%2C%20felt%20like%20one%20of%20his%20more%20personal%20films.%20And%20now%2C%20in%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Killer%2C%20%3C%2Fem%3Eit%20feels%20like%20Fincher%20is%20looking%20inwards%20more%20than%20outwards%20for%20inspiration.%20Even%20his%20choice%20of%20actor%2C%20Michael%20Fassbender%2C%20who%20was%20brought%20out%20of%20hibernation%20after%20being%20chewed%20out%20in%20six%20consecutive%20studio%20flops%2C%20seems%20to%20be%20telling%20its%20own%20story.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAdapted%20from%20a%20French%20graphic%20novel%20of%20the%20same%20name%20by%20Alexis%20%E2%80%98Matz%E2%80%99%20Nolent%2C%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Killer%3C%2Fem%3E%20opens%20with%20the%20protagonist%20talking%20about%20how%20contract%20killing%20isn%E2%80%99t%20a%20job%20worth%20pursuing%20if%20you%20can%E2%80%99t%20endure%20the%20waiting.%20He%20could%20be%20talking%20about%20filmmaking%20itself%20%E2%80%93%20a%20vocation%20about%20which%20actor%20John%20Candy%20once%20remarked%3A%20%E2%80%9CI%20get%20paid%20for%20waiting%2C%20I%20throw%20in%20the%20acting%20for%20free!%E2%80%9D%20This%20is%20Fincher%20at%20his%20most%20indulgent%20%E2%80%93%20sharing%20his%20philosophies%20with%20the%20world%20through%20a%20protagonist%20who%20is%20as%20dry%2C%20disciplined%2C%20meticulous%20and%20proud%20as%20a%20craftsman%20as%20the%20filmmaker%20is.%20Over%20the%20normal%20course%20of%20events%2C%20the%20protagonist%20dispassionately%20looks%20at%20life%20as%20something%20to%20endure.%20It%E2%80%99s%20a%20self-centered%20way%20of%20living%20saying%20%E2%80%9CI%20don%E2%80%99t%20give%20a%20damn%E2%80%9D%20about%20anything%20that%20doesn%E2%80%99t%20help%20him%20in%20his%20work.%20That%E2%80%99s%20until%20someone%20hurts%20a%20loved%20one.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFincher%20takes%20the%20template%20of%20hitman%20films%20like%20%3Cem%3EJason%20Bourne%3C%2Fem%3E%20or%20%3Cem%3EJohn%20Wick%3C%2Fem%3E%20%E2%80%93%C2%A0%20slowly%20draining%20all%20the%20sexiness%20out%20of%20it.%20It%20seems%20a%20very%20deliberate%20choice%2C%20where%20he%20takes%20the%20very%20template%20of%20a%20genre%20he%20has%20helped%20establish%2C%20and%20turns%20it%20inside%20out.%20Fassbender%20%E2%80%93%20who%20hasn%E2%80%99t%20starred%20in%20movies%20in%20three%20years%20%E2%80%93%20seems%20to%20be%20enjoying%20his%20director%E2%80%99s%20quiet%20rebellion%20against%20what%20is%20expected%20of%20a%20%E2%80%98cool%E2%80%99%20Fincher%20film.%20He%E2%80%99s%20dressed%20and%20styled%20unmemorably%20throughout%2C%20in%20Khakis%2C%20tracksuits%2C%20baseball%20caps.%20Even%20though%20there%E2%80%99s%20the%20usual%20globetrotting%20in%20a%20film%20like%20this%2C%20where%20the%20killer%20hops%20on%20transcontinental%20flights%20like%20they%20were%20local%20trains%20in%20Bombay%2C%20Fincher%20never%20milks%20the%20changing%20geography%20with%20the%20cliched%20top-shot%20of%20a%20city%2C%20with%20the%20name%20appearing%20as%20a%20title%20card%20on%20screen.%20Instead%2C%20he%20makes%20mundane%20observations%20about%20them%20like%20any%20world-weary%20traveller%3A%20%E2%80%9CParis%20is%20a%20city%20that%20wakes%20up%20slowly%E2%80%9D%2C%20%E2%80%9CNew%20Orleans%2C%20a%20thousand%20restaurants%E2%80%A6%20one%20menu.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThere%E2%80%99s%20one%20fist%20fight%20sequence%20in%20the%20entire%20film%20%E2%80%93%20and%20it%20seems%20to%20be%20designed%20in%20a%20way%20to%20look%20functional%2C%20not%20stylish.%20However%2C%20Fincher%E2%80%99s%20precision%20shows%20up%20in%20the%20closing%20moments%20of%20the%20scene%2C%20when%20the%20killer%20needs%20to%20escape%20a%20pitbull.%20The%20timing%20and%20choreography%20of%20this%20last%20bit%20is%20unsurprisingly%20exquisite.%20There%E2%80%99s%20a%20scene%20featuring%20%E2%80%98The%20Expert%E2%80%99%20(Tilda%20Swinton)%2C%20where%20Fincher%20clasps%20the%20breaks%20on%20the%20film%2C%20allowing%20someone%20other%20than%20his%20protagonist%20to%20ruminate%20on%20their%20choices.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhy%20do%20we%20do%20the%20things%20we%20do%3F%20Even%20while%20paying%20the%20price%20of%20our%20mental%20well-being%2C%20battling%20unfavourable%20situations%2C%20choosing%20our%20calling%20over%20an%20impersonal%20job%20that%20will%20help%20us%20lead%20a%20sane%2C%20bloodless%2C%20probably%20boring%20life%3F%20Are%20we%20all%20masochists%3F%20It%E2%80%99s%20a%20sequence%20worthy%20of%20Tilda%20Swinton%E2%80%99s%20starry%20presence%2C%20when%20she%20makes%20her%20moves%20with%20words%20and%20glances.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThe%20Killer%3C%2Fem%3E%20might%20suggest%20that%20Fincher%20is%20grappling%20with%20his%20own%20label%20as%20a%20cold%2C%20clinical%20genius%2C%20who%20prioritises%20perfection%20over%20vulnerability%2C%20precision%20over%20humanity.%20However%2C%20as%20the%20climax%20of%20the%20film%20suggests%2C%20he%20wants%20to%20continue%20doing%20what%20he%20loves%2C%20even%20as%20his%20disdain%20for%20having%20to%20fight%20for%20his%20terms%20might%20be%20starting%20to%20take%20a%20toll%20on%20him.%20Unlike%20what%20many%20of%20his%20fans%20think%2C%20Fincher%20sees%20himself%20as%20a%20part%20of%20the%20many.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDeep%20down%20somewhere%2C%20despite%20what%20he%20has%20said%20in%20the%20past%2C%20David%20Fincher%20still%20gives%20a%20f%23%24k.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1699875042000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F13161217%2Fimage-1495.png%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Ffilm%2Fthe-killer-the-clinical-assassin-in-a-film-made-by-a-clinical-director-david-fincher%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20film%20reflects%20the%20disdain%20the%20director%20has%20felt%20over%20the%20years%20for%20Hollywood%20studios%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A15%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Ffilm%2Fthe-killer-the-clinical-assassin-in-a-film-made-by-a-clinical-director-david-fincher%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22How%20India%20Is%20Shifting%20Its%20Nuclear%20Power%20Plans%20Into%20High%20Gear%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2019%2F10%2F03162440%2Fimage-1.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3EOn%20December%2014%20last%20year%2C%20Union%20minister%20of%20state%20for%20Atomic%20Energy%20and%20Space%20Jitendra%20Singh%20made%20an%20announcement%20with%20far-reaching%20consequences.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20written%20reply%20to%20the%20Lok%20Sabha%2C%20Singh%20said%20the%20Bharatiya%20Janata%20Party-led%20NDA%20government%20will%20commission%2020%20new%20nuclear%20reactors%20by%202031.%20With%20that%2C%20he%20said%2C%20India%E2%80%99s%20installed%20nuclear%20capacity%20will%20treble%20from%20the%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Findia%2F20-new-nuclear-plants-to-be-commissioned-in-country-by-2031-minister-in-lok-sabha%2Farticleshow%2F96232288.cms%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecurrent%207%2C480%20megawatt%20(MW)%20to%2022%2C480%20MW%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETen%20of%20these%20reactors%20%E2%80%93%20like%20the%20500%20MW%20Prototype%20Fast%20Breeder%20Reactor%20at%20Kalpakkam%20and%20the%20two%201%2C000%20MW%20reactors%20at%20Kudankulam%20%E2%80%93%20are%20already%20under%20construction.%20In%20addition%2C%20the%20government%20has%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Findia%2F20-new-nuclear-plants-to-be-commissioned-in-country-by-2031-minister-in-lok-sabha%2Farticleshow%2F96232288.cms%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Egranted%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0%E2%80%9Cadministrative%20and%20financial%20sanctions%E2%80%9D%20for%20building%2010%20more%20nuclear%20plants%20with%20700%20MW%20Pressurised%20Heavy%20Water%20Reactors%20at%20Gorakhpur%20(Haryana)%2C%20Kaiga%20(Karnataka)%2C%20Chutka%20(Madhya%20Pradesh)%20and%20Mahi%20Banswara%20(Rajasthan).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThat%20is%20just%20the%20start.%20Another%20clutch%20of%20reactors%20have%20secured%20in-principle%20approvals.%20Once%20all%20these%20projects%20are%20up%2C%20the%20number%20of%20India%E2%80%99s%20nuclear%20reactors%20will%20rise%20from%20the%20current%2022%20to%20well%20above%2050.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThat%20is%20not%20all.%20The%20NDA%20government%20is%20also%20bullish%20on%20SMRs%2C%20typically%20below%20300%20MW%20in%20capacity%2C%20and%20wants%20to%20use%20them%20for%20both%20power%20generation%20and%20to%20decarbonise%20industry.%20National%20Thermal%20Power%20Corporation%20(NTPC)%20is%20thinking%20of%C2%A0%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thehindubusinessline.com%2Fcompanies%2Fpower-giant-ntpc-to-build-nuclear-fleet-to-aid-climate-goal-chase%2Farticle66238287.ece%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eretro-fitting%20small%20modular%20reactors%20(SMRs)%20into%20decommissioned%20coal%20plants%3C%2Fa%3E.%20In%20August%2C%20speaking%20at%20a%20conclave%20on%20green%20hydrogen%20and%20net%20zero%2C%20senior%20NITI%20Aayog%20official%20V.K.%20Saraswat%20said%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Feducation%2Fnews%2Fadvancing-indias-net-zero-mission-conclave-explores-green-hydrogen-production%2Farticleshow%2F102712272.cms%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eindustrial%20units%20too%20should%20use%20SMRs%20to%20produce%20hydrogen%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESome%20of%20the%20projected%20numbers%20are%20mind-boggling.%20The%20installed%20capacity%20of%20coal-fired%20plants%20in%20India%20stands%20around%20220%20gigawatt%20(GW).%20%E2%80%9C%5BOf%20this%20220%20GW%5D%2C%2020%20GW%20is%20already%20off%20the%20grid%20and%20gradually%20others%20will%20also%20be%20coming%20in%20the%20line%2C%E2%80%9D%20A.K.%20Nayak%2C%20head%20(Nuclear%20Control%20and%20Program%20Wing)%20at%20the%20Department%20of%20Atomic%20Energy%20said%20last%20December%20at%20a%20conference%20organised%20by%20India%20Nuclear%20Business%20Platform%2C%20a%20nuclear%20power%20advocacy%20firm%20owned%20by%20a%20Singapore-based%20consultancy%20called%20Industry%20Platform.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThese%2C%20he%20said%2C%20can%20be%20refitted%20with%20SMRs.%20%E2%80%9CThere%20is%20a%20big%20opportunity%20for%20SMRs%20in%20a%20span%20of%202-3%20decades%E2%80%A6%20For%20interested%20companies%20like%20NTPC%20and%20others%20it%20is%20a%20business%20opportunity%20of%20220%20GW.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EGoing%20by%20such%20projections%2C%20SMRs%20might%20play%20a%20bigger%20role%20in%20India%20than%20large%20reactors.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch4%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-kadence-advancedheading%5C%22%20data-kb-block%3D%5C%22kb-adv-heading_4badb5-27%5C%22%3ET%3Cstrong%3Ehe%20case%20for%20nuclear%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh4%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20curious%20silence%20has%20accompanied%20most%20of%20these%20plans.%20Barring%20the%C2%A0%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fhow-india-plans-to-use-nuclear-power-to-achieve-net-zero-emissions-international-atomic-energy-agency-vienna-4430090%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eodd%20media%20report%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0outlining%20the%20government%E2%80%99s%20plans%20for%20nuclear%20power%20and%C2%A0%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thehindubusinessline.com%2Fmultimedia%2Fvideo%2Fwhy-small-modular-reactors-are-key-to-indias-decarbonisation-goals%2Farticle67187868.ece%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eop-eds%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0in%C2%A0%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Findianexpress.com%2Farticle%2Fexplained%2Fexplained-economics%2Fnuclear-power-space-india-strategic-sectors-private-8930052%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Efavour%20of%20SMRs%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20there%20has%20not%20been%20enough%20critical%20discussion%20around%20this%20proposed%20nuclear%20buildup.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ECan%20nuclear%20energy%20help%20India%20step%20away%20from%20coal%3F%20Has%20the%20industry%20resolved%20its%20old%20problems%20with%20cost-%20and%20time-overruns%3F%20What%20about%20public%20safety%3F%20Given%20the%20world%20continues%20to%20innovate%20in%20renewables%2C%20should%20India%20go%20for%20100%25%20renewables%20or%20push%20to%20add%20nuclear%20capacity%20as%20well%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20the%20energy%20front%2C%20the%20country%20is%20stuck%20between%20a%20rock%20and%20a%20hard%20place.%20In%202022-23%2C%20its%20power%20demand%20stood%20at%C2%A0%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Feconomictimes.indiatimes.com%2Findustry%2Fenergy%2Fpower-consumption-grows-9-5-pc-to-1503-billion-units-in-2022-23-govt-data%2Farticleshow%2F99530203.cms%3Ffrom%3Dmdr%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E1%2C503%20billion%20units%3C%2Fa%3E%20(BUs).%20This%20demand%20was%20met%20through%20an%20installed%20power%20generation%20capacity%20of%20415.4%20GW%2C%20with%20236.68%20GW%20coming%20from%20coal%2C%20lignite%20and%20gas.%20Renewables%20%E2%80%93%20hydel%2C%20solar%2C%20bio-energy%2C%20wind%20and%20pumped%20storage%20%E2%80%93%20accounted%20for%20171.8%20GW.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20India%20decarbonises%2C%20not%20only%20will%20most%20of%20these%20thermal%20units%20be%20wound%20down%2C%20the%20country%20will%20also%20see%20additional%20demand%20for%20electricity%20as%20other%20users%20of%20hydrocarbons%20%E2%80%93%20like%20factories%20and%20vehicles%20%E2%80%93%20electrify%20as%20well.%20By%202030%2C%20India%E2%80%99s%20Central%20Electricity%20Authority%20expects%20the%20country%E2%80%99s%20electricity%20demand%20to%20touch%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcea.nic.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2Firp%2F2023%2F05%2FOptimal_mix_report__2029_30_Version_2.0__For_Uploading.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E2%2C279%20BU%3C%2Fa%3E.%20By%202050%2C%20says%C2%A0%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.energymonitor.ai%2Fpolicy%2Fhow-india-could-reach-net-zero-by-2050%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EEnergy%20Monitor%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20power%20demand%20might%20touch%205%2C921%20BUs.%20At%20this%20point%2C%20the%20country%20might%20need%20as%20much%20as%204%2C000%20GW%20of%20installed%20capacity%20%E2%80%93%20almost%20a%2010-fold%20jump%20from%20today.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThat%20is%20where%20a%20massive%20constraint%20asserts%20itself.%20India%E2%80%99s%20potential%20RE%20capacity%20%E2%80%93%20between%20hydel%2C%20solar%20and%20wind%20%E2%80%93%20is%20currently%20estimated%20at%20no%20more%20than%201%2C000%20GW.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20gets%20worse.%20The%20country%20cannot%20build%20to%20full%20potential%20capacity%20%E2%80%93%20building%20145%2C000%20MW%20of%20dams%20will%20extract%20its%20own%20social%20and%20ecological%20costs.%20As%20will%20unfettered%20expansion%20of%20solar%20parks%20and%20wind%20farms.%20India%20can%20reduce%20total%20future%20power%20demand%20%E2%80%93%20by%20slashing%20transmission%20and%20distribution%20losses%20or%20by%20providing%20Indians%20lower%20per%20capita%20power%20than%20the%20global%20average%20by%20embracing%20greater%20energy%20efficiency%20%E2%80%93%20but%20there%20will%20still%20be%20a%20shortfall.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOne%20morning%20in%20April%2C%20seeking%20to%20understand%20all%20this%20better%2C%20%3Cem%3ECarbonCopy%3C%2Fem%3E%20met%20nuclear%20scientist%20Ravi%20Grover%20at%20his%20office%20in%20Mumbai%E2%80%99s%20Bhabha%20Atomic%20Research%20Centre.%20Given%20the%20size%20of%20its%20population%2C%20he%20said%20in%20that%20chat%2C%20India%20will%20have%20to%20use%20all%20the%20energy%20options%20with%20her.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThat%20morning%2C%20Grover%20outlined%20another%20reason%20why%20India%20needs%20nuclear%20power.%20In%20the%20past%2C%20power%20supply%20was%20constant%20(thanks%20to%20thermal%20power%20plants)%20while%20demand%20waxed%20and%20waned.%20%E2%80%9CBalance%20between%20supply%20and%20demand%20was%20usually%20maintained%20through%20load-shedding%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20told%20%3Cem%3ECarbonCopy%3C%2Fem%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThat%20is%20changing%20now%2C%20he%20said.%20As%20the%20share%20of%20renewables%20in%20India%E2%80%99s%20energy%20mix%20rises%2C%20both%20supply%20and%20demand%20will%20become%20variable.%20The%20country%E2%80%99s%20electricity%20system%20will%20need%20additional%20investments%20%E2%80%93%20pumped%20storage%2C%20battery%20storage%2C%20electrolysers%2C%20what%20have%20you%20%E2%80%93%20to%20balance%20demand%20and%20supply.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDelivering%20what%20Grover%20describes%20in%C2%A0%3Cem%3E%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.currentscience.ac.in%2FVolumes%2F123%2F11%2F1309.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ECurrent%20Science%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%C2%A0as%20%E2%80%9Cfirm%20power%E2%80%9D%2C%20nuclear%20power%20can%20also%20help%20address%20intermittency.%20%E2%80%9CIf%20India%20wants%20200%20GW%20of%20renewable%20power%2C%20then%20we%20should%20try%20to%20have%2020-40%20GW%20of%20nuclear%20as%20well%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20told%20%3Cem%3ECarbonCopy.%3C%2Fem%3E%20%E2%80%9CThat%20is%20what%20the%20world%20is%20doing.%20The%20UK%20will%20be%2025%25%20nuclear%20by%20the%20middle%20of%20this%20century.%20France%20is%20adding%20eight%20to%2014%20new%20reactors.%20India%2C%20too%2C%20needs%20to%20add%20three%20to%20four%20times%20as%20much%20nuclear%20capacity.%20What%20we%20have%20is%20not%20enough.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThere%20is%2C%20however%2C%20one%20big%20problem.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch4%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-kadence-advancedheading%5C%22%20data-kb-block%3D%5C%22kb-adv-heading_36307d-6c%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EBroken%20promises%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh4%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20is%20not%20the%20first%20time%20India%20has%20mapped%20out%20a%20large%20buildup%20of%20nuclear%20capacity.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20past%2C%20too%2C%20variably%20citing%20military%20security%2C%20energy%20security%20and%20looming%20energy%20shortages%2C%20India%E2%80%99s%20nuclear%20establishment%20has%20pushed%20for%C2%A0%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcasi.sas.upenn.edu%2Fiit%2Framana%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Erapid%20expansion%20of%20the%20country%E2%80%99s%20nuclear%20power%20capacity%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%201954%2C%20Homi%20Bhabha%2C%20the%20founder%20of%20India%E2%80%99s%20nuclear%20programme%2C%20said%20India%20would%20have%208%2C000%20MW%20of%20nuclear%20capacity%20by%201980.%20In%201960%2C%20the%20country%20was%20told%20it%20would%20have%2043%2C500%20MW%20by%202000.%20In%201984%2C%20a%20decade%20after%20the%201974%20nuclear%20test%2C%20the%20country%20was%20promised%2010%2C000%20MW%20by%202000.%20The%20actual%20installed%20capacity%20was%20about%20600%20MW%20in%201980%20and%202%2C720%20MW%20in%202000.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%201999%2C%20India%E2%80%99s%20nuclear%20establishment%20said%20the%20country%20would%20have%2020%2C000%20MW%20by%202020.%20In%20the%20early%202000s%2C%20the%20DAE%20(Department%20of%20Atomic%20Energy)%20upped%20that%20target%20to%20275%20GW%20by%202052%20%E2%80%93%20and%20then%20to%20470%20GW%20after%20the%20US-India%20nuclear%20deal.%20India%20missed%20those%20targets%20as%20well.%20Today%2C%20the%20country%E2%80%99s%20installed%20nuclear%20capacity%20stands%20at%207%2C480%20MW.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20clutch%20of%20factors%20are%20responsible%20for%20this%20under-delivery.%20Some%20are%20global.%20India%E2%80%99s%20nuclear%20tests%20left%20the%20country%20struggling%20to%20source%20technology%20and%20nuclear%20fuels.%20In%20more%20recent%20years%2C%20the%20Nuclear%20Liability%20Act%20has%20dissuaded%20foreign%20nuclear%20suppliers%20from%20entering%20the%20market.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOthers%20are%20local.%20As%20physicist%20M.V.%20Ramana%20wrote%20in%20%3Cem%3E%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fpenguin.co.in%2Fbook%2Fthe-power-of-promise%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EThe%20Power%20of%20Promise%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20his%202012%20book%20on%20India%E2%80%99s%20nuclear%20power%20aspirations%2C%20lack%20of%20scale%20has%20been%20a%20problem.%20%E2%80%9CThe%20problem%20was%20not%20that%20the%20industry%20lacked%20the%20technological%20base%20needed%20to%20carry%20out%20the%20fabrication%20%5Bof%20the%20reactors%5D%2C%20but%20that%20the%20few%20orders%20that%20it%20received%20from%20the%20DAE%20did%20not%20make%20it%20economical%20for%20companies%20to%20do%20so.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELand%20acquisition%20has%20been%20another%20bugbear.%20Design%20changes%20during%20construction%20are%20yet%20another.%20In%20all%2C%20as%20Ramana%20wrote%2C%20India%E2%80%99s%20nuclear%20plants%20have%20been%20plagued%20by%20cost-%20and%20time-overruns%2C%20and%20performed%20worse%20than%20envisaged.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20is%20where%20things%20get%20interesting.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch4%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-kadence-advancedheading%5C%22%20data-kb-block%3D%5C%22kb-adv-heading_44012e-94%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EStepping%20around%20past%20glitches%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh4%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETo%20ensure%20the%20latest%20nuclear%20buildup%20doesn%E2%80%99t%20meet%20the%20fate%20of%20its%20predecessors%2C%20the%20BJP-led%20NDA%20government%20has%20made%20two%20changes.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFirst%2C%20Nuclear%20Power%20Corporation%20of%20India%20(NPCIL)%20has%20been%20told%20to%20jointly%20develop%20nuclear%20plants%20with%20firms%20like%20NTPC.%20The%20rationale%3F%20Not%20only%20can%20NTPC%20raise%20funds%20more%20easily%20than%20NPCIL%2C%20by%20pooling%20their%20strengths%20in%20project%20management%20and%20nuclear%20plant%20design%2C%20NPCIL%20and%20NTPC%20can%20set%20up%20nuclear%20plants%20faster.%20This%20point%20was%20made%20at%20the%20India%20Nuclear%20Business%20Platform%20conference%20last%20December.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CEarlier%20NPCIL%20was%20executing%20one%20or%20two%20projects%20at%20a%20time%2C%20but%20now%20with%20capacity%20getting%20ramped%20up%20substantially%2C%20the%20plan%20is%20that%20NPCIL%20along%20with%20NTPC%20will%20be%20running%20at%20least%2010%20nuclear%20projects%20at%20a%20time%2C%E2%80%9D%20said%20R.%20Sharan%2C%20director%20(projects)%2C%20NPCIL.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESecond%2C%20seeking%20to%20obviate%20risks%20like%20time%2Fcost%20overruns%20and%20the%20difficulty%20of%20land%20acquisition%2C%20the%20NDA%20is%20bullish%20on%20SMRs.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20tandem%2C%20it%20is%20also%20getting%20easier%20for%20India%20to%20source%20nuclear%20technology%20from%20outside.%20As%20nuclear%20energy%20tries%20to%20regain%20ground%20lost%20to%20renewables%2C%20a%20bevy%20of%20large%20reactor%20makers%20and%20SMR%20manufacturers%20are%20competing%20to%20crack%20markets%20like%20India.%20Anyone%20trying%20to%20understand%20the%20role%20of%20nuclear%20in%20India%E2%80%99s%20emerging%20energy%20mix%20has%20to%20engage%20with%20these%20shifts%20in%20policy.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETwo%20questions%2C%20therefore%2C%20arise.%20Both%20the%20NPCIL-NTPC%20alliance%20and%20SMRs%20are%20untested%20experiments.%20Can%20they%20deliver%3F%20Further%2C%C2%A0%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.cell.com%2Fjoule%2Ffulltext%2FS2542-4351(23)00281-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ethe%20competitive%20landscape%20for%20nuclear%20power%20is%20changing%3C%2Fa%3E.%20It%20no%20longer%20competes%20with%20coal%20and%20gas.%20Instead%2C%20billions%20are%20being%20spent%20to%20boost%20efficiency%20of%20existing%20renewable%20technologies%20like%20solar%20panels%2C%20wind%20turbines%2C%20rechargeable%20batteries%20and%20develop%20newer%20sources%20of%20renewable%20power%20like%20electrolysers.%20Countries%20are%20also%20experimenting%20with%20technologies%20like%20pumped%20storage%20and%20grid%20management%20to%20create%20100%25%20renewable%20grids.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESo%20can%20SMRs%E2%80%94and%20NTPC%E2%80%94carve%20out%20a%20perch%20for%20nuclear%20power%20in%20India%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20second%20part%20of%20the%20series%20will%20look%20into%20this%20question.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThis%20article%20was%20originally%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcarboncopy.info%2Fhow-india-is-shifting-its-nuclear-power-plans-into-high-gear%2F%5C%22%3Epublished%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%3C%2Fem%3E%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcarboncopy.info%2F%5C%22%3ECarbon%20Copy%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1699874152000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2019%2F10%2F03162440%2Fimage-1.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fenergy%2Fhow-india-is-shifting-its-nuclear-power-plans-into-high-gear%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20country%20needs%20to%20decarbonise.%20Its%20renewables%20face%20charges%20of%20intermittency.%20Is%20nuclear%20the%20answer%3F%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A9%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fenergy%2Fhow-india-is-shifting-its-nuclear-power-plans-into-high-gear%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Trade%20Unions%20Denounce%20Israeli%20Call%20to%20Replace%20Palestinian%20Workers%2C%20Urge%20India%20to%20Reject%20Request%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F13152108%2Fimage-1494.png%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENew%20Delhi%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20In%20a%20strongly%20worded%20joint%20statement%20issued%20on%20November%209%2C%20ten%20major%20trade%20unions%20in%20India%2C%20under%20the%20banner%20of%20the%20Joint%20Platform%20of%20Central%20Trade%20Unions%20and%20Independent%20Federations%2C%20called%20on%20the%20Indian%20government%20to%20reject%20Israel%E2%80%99s%20construction%20sector%E2%80%99s%20request%20to%20replace%20Palestinian%20workers%20with%20Indian%20workers%20amid%20the%20ongoing%20war%20on%20Gaza.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFollowing%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fdiplomacy%2Fjaishankar-hamas-israel-india-palestine%5C%22%3EOctober%207%20attacks%20against%20Israel%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20tens%20of%20thousands%20of%20Palestinian%20workers%20in%20the%20Israeli%20construction%20industry%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.npr.org%2F2023%2F11%2F04%2F1210588361%2Fisrael-palestinian-workers-construction-economy%5C%22%3Ehave%20been%20suspended%3C%2Fa%3E.%20%3Cem%3EVoice%20of%20America%3C%2Fem%3E%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.voanews.com%2Fa%2Fisraeli-construction-sector-moves-to-replace-palestinian-employees-with-indian-workers%2F7338259.html%5C%22%3Ereported%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20Israel%E2%80%99s%20construction%20sector%20had%20urged%20the%20Indian%20government%20to%20allow%20companies%20to%20hire%20up%20to%20100%2C000%20workers%20from%20India%20to%20replace%20the%2090%2C000%20Palestinians%20who%20roughly%20form%20about%2025%25%20of%20the%20workforce%20in%20the%20sector.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20November%209%2C%20Ministry%20of%20External%20Affairs%20spokesperson%20Arindam%20Bagchi%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.mea.gov.in%2Fmedia-briefings.htm%3Fdtl%2F37250%2FTranscript%2Bof%2BWeekly%2BMedia%2BBriefing%2Bby%2Bthe%2BOfficial%2BSpokesperson%2BNovember%2B09%2B2023%5C%22%3Esaid%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20he%20is%20not%20aware%20of%20any%20such%20particular%20request%20from%20Israel.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CWith%20Israel%2C%20there%20are%20already%20a%20number%20of%20Indian%20workers%20employed%20there%2C%20especially%20in%20the%20caregiver%20sector.%20Since%2C%20I%20think%2C%202022%2C%20we%20have%20been%20discussing%20a%20bilateral%20framework%20in%20the%20construction%20and%20caregiver%20sectors%2C%20but%20this%20is%20a%20long-term%20initiative%20and%20I%20am%20not%2C%20as%20I%20said%2C%20aware%20of%20any%20specific%20requests%20or%20numbers%20that%20have%20been%20floating%20around%2C%E2%80%9D%20Bagchi%20said%2C%20per%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.mea.gov.in%2Fmedia-briefings.htm%3Fdtl%2F37250%2FTranscript%2Bof%2BWeekly%2BMedia%2BBriefing%2Bby%2Bthe%2BOfficial%2BSpokesperson%2BNovember%2B09%2B2023%5C%22%3Etranscript%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20the%20media%20briefing%20on%20the%20MEA%20website.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20joint%20platform%20of%20independent%20trade%20unions%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.publicnow.com%2Fview%2F7B8FE8056D3A516B8906DE8A0B88B7BD5E641B74%5C%22%3Ecriticised%3C%2Fa%3E%20the%20Modi%20government%E2%80%99s%20stand%20on%20the%20conflict%20as%20%E2%80%9Cunethical%E2%80%9D%20and%20%E2%80%9Cduplicitous%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CNothing%20could%20be%20more%20immoral%20and%20disastrous%20for%20India%20than%20the%20said%20%E2%80%9Cexport%E2%80%9D%20of%20workers%20to%20Israel.%20That%20India%20is%20even%20considering%20%E2%80%9Cexporting%E2%80%9D%20workers%20shows%20the%20manner%20in%20which%20it%20has%20dehumanised%20and%20commodified%20Indian%20workers.%20Such%20a%20step%20will%20amount%20to%20complicity%20on%20India%E2%80%99s%20part%20with%20Israel%E2%80%99s%20ongoing%20genocidal%20war%20against%20Palestinians%20and%20will%20naturally%20have%20adverse%20implications%20for%20Indian%20workers%20in%20the%20entire%20region%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.publicnow.com%2Fview%2F7B8FE8056D3A516B8906DE8A0B88B7BD5E641B74%5C%22%3Epress%20release%3C%2Fa%3E%20issued%20by%20the%20platform%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDescribing%20Israel%E2%80%99s%20war%20on%20Gaza%20as%20%E2%80%9Cshamelessly%20genocidal%E2%80%9D%2C%20the%20trade%20unions%20have%20called%20upon%20Indian%20workers%20to%20show%20solidarity%20with%20Palestinian%20workers%20and%20refuse%20to%20replace%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CIndia%E2%80%99s%20trade%20union%20movement%20must%20rise%20in%20solidarity%20with%20Palestinian%20workers%20and%20reject%20this%20disastrous%20idea.%20Let%E2%80%99s%20resolve%20that%20we%20will%20not%20work%20to%20replace%20Palestinian%20workers%20in%20Israel%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20joint%20statement%20said.%20It%20has%20also%20called%20upon%20Indian%20workers%20to%20boycott%20Israeli%20products%20and%20to%20refuse%20to%20handle%20the%20Israeli%20cargo.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1699873223000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F13152108%2Fimage-1494.png%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Frights%2Ftrade-unions-denounce-israeli-call-to-replace-palestinian-workers-urge-india-to-reject-request%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22However%2C%20Ministry%20of%20External%20Affairs%20spokesperson%20Arindam%20Bagchi%20said%20that%20he%20is%20not%20aware%20of%20any%20such%20particular%20request%20from%20Israel.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A9%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Frights%2Ftrade-unions-denounce-israeli-call-to-replace-palestinian-workers-urge-india-to-reject-request%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22The%20Rise%20and%20Fall%20of%20Antibiotics%3A%20What%20Would%20a%20Post-Antibiotic%20World%20Look%20Like%3F%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F09170130%2Fsj-objio-8hHxO3iYuU0-unsplash.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3EThese%20days%2C%20we%20don%E2%80%99t%20think%20much%20about%20being%20able%20to%20access%20a%20course%20of%20antibiotics%20to%20head%20off%20an%20infection.%20But%20that%20wasn%E2%80%99t%20always%20the%20case%20%E2%80%93%20antibiotics%20have%20been%20available%20for%20less%20than%20a%20century.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBefore%20that%2C%20patients%20would%20die%20of%20relatively%20trivial%20infections%20that%20became%20more%20serious.%20Some%20serious%20infections%2C%20such%20as%20those%20involving%20the%20heart%20valves%2C%20were%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fpubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov%2F20173297%2F%5C%22%3Einevitably%3C%2Fa%3E%20fatal.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOther%20serious%20infections%2C%20such%20as%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov%2Fpmc%2Farticles%2FPMC3070694%2F%5C%22%3Etuberculosis%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20weren%E2%80%99t%20always%20fatal.%20Up%20to%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.biorxiv.org%2Fcontent%2F10.1101%2F729426v1.full.pdf%5C%22%3Ehalf%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20people%20died%20within%20a%20year%20with%20the%20most%20severe%20forms%2C%20but%20some%20people%20recovered%20without%20treatment%20and%20the%20remainder%20had%20ongoing%20chronic%20infection%20that%20slowly%20ate%20away%20at%20the%20body%20over%20many%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOnce%20we%20had%20antibiotics%2C%20the%20outcomes%20for%20these%20infections%20were%20much%20better.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ELife%20(and%20death)%20before%20antibiotics%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EYou%E2%80%99ve%20probably%20heard%20of%20Alexander%20Fleming%E2%80%99s%20accidental%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.acs.org%2Feducation%2Fwhatischemistry%2Flandmarks%2Fflemingpenicillin.html%5C%22%3Ediscovery%20of%20penicillin%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20when%20fungal%20spores%20landed%20on%20a%20plate%20with%20bacteria%20left%20over%20a%20long%20weekend%20in%201928.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ox.ac.uk%2Fnews%2Fscience-blog%2Fpenicillin-oxford-story%5C%22%3Efirst%20patient%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20receive%20penicillin%20was%20an%20instructive%20example%20of%20the%20impact%20of%20treatment.%3Cbr%3E%5CnIn%201941%2C%20Constable%20Albert%20Alexander%20had%20a%20scratch%20on%20his%20face%20that%20had%20become%20infected.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20was%20hospitalised%20but%20despite%20various%20treatments%2C%20the%20infection%20progressed%20to%20involve%20his%20head.%20This%20required%20removing%20one%20of%20his%20eyes.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F09170106%2Fpexels-jonathan-borba-13083355.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F09170106%2Fpexels-jonathan-borba-13083355.jpg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F09170106%2Fpexels-jonathan-borba-13083355-300x200.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F09170106%2Fpexels-jonathan-borba-13083355-1024x683.jpg%201024w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-684313%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22800%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EIn%201941%2C%20Albert%20Alexander%20was%20hospitalised%20with%20a%20severe%20infection.%20Photo%3A%20Jonathan%20Borba%2FPexels%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHoward%20Florey%2C%20the%20Australian%20pharmacologist%20then%20working%20in%20Oxford%2C%20was%20concerned%20penicillin%20could%20be%20toxic%20in%20humans.%20Therefore%2C%20he%20felt%20it%20was%20only%20ethical%20to%20give%20this%20new%20drug%20to%20a%20patient%20in%20a%20desperate%20condition.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EConstable%20Alexander%20was%20given%20the%20available%20dose%20of%20penicillin.%20Within%20the%20first%20day%2C%20his%20condition%20had%20started%20to%20improve.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20back%20then%2C%20penicillin%20was%20difficult%20to%20produce.%20One%20way%20of%20extending%20the%20limited%20supply%20was%20to%20%E2%80%9Crecycle%E2%80%9D%20penicillin%20that%20was%20excreted%20in%20the%20patient%E2%80%99s%20urine.%20Despite%20this%2C%20supplies%20ran%20out%20by%20the%20fifth%20day%20of%20Alexander%E2%80%99s%20treatment.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWithout%20further%20treatment%2C%20the%20infection%20again%20took%20hold.%20Constable%20Alexander%20eventually%20died%20a%20month%20later.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWe%20now%20face%20a%20world%20where%20we%20are%20potentially%20running%20out%20of%20antibiotics%20%E2%80%93%20not%20because%20of%20difficulties%20manufacturing%20them%2C%20but%20because%20they%E2%80%99re%20losing%20their%20effectiveness.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhat%20do%20we%20use%20antibiotics%20for%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWe%20currently%20use%20antibiotics%20in%20humans%20and%20animals%20for%20a%20variety%20of%20reasons.%20Antibiotics%20reduce%20the%20duration%20of%20illness%20and%20the%20chance%20of%20death%20from%20infection.%20They%20also%20prevent%20infections%20in%20people%20who%20are%20at%20high%20risk%2C%20such%20as%20patients%20undergoing%20surgery%20and%20those%20with%20weakened%20immune%20systems.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20antibiotics%20aren%E2%80%99t%20always%20used%20appropriately.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thelancet.com%2Fjournals%2Flaninf%2Farticle%2FPIIS1473-3099(20)30084-0%2Ffulltext%5C%22%3EStudies%3C%2Fa%3E%20consistently%20show%20a%20dose%20or%20two%20will%20adequately%20prevent%20infections%20after%20surgery%2C%20but%20antibiotics%20are%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Firp.cdn-website.com%2Fd820f98f%2Ffiles%2Fuploaded%2Fsurgical-prophylaxis-prescribing-in-australian-hospitals-results-of-the-2020-surgical-national-antimicrobial-prescribing-survey.pdf%5C%22%3Eoften%3C%2Fa%3E%20continued%20for%20several%20days%20unnecessarily.%20And%20sometimes%20we%20use%20the%20wrong%20type%20of%20antibiotic.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Firp.cdn-website.com%2Fd820f98f%2Ffiles%2Fuploaded%2Fantimicrobial-prescribing-practice-in-australian-hospitals-results-of-the-2020-hospital-national-antimicrobial-prescribing-survey.pdf%5C%22%3ESurveys%3C%2Fa%3E%20have%20found%2022%25%20of%20antimicrobial%20use%20in%20hospitals%20is%20inappropriate.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F09170116%2Fnational-cancer-institute-fTQHPb6r4wQ-unsplash.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F09170116%2Fnational-cancer-institute-fTQHPb6r4wQ-unsplash.jpg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F09170116%2Fnational-cancer-institute-fTQHPb6r4wQ-unsplash-300x200.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F09170116%2Fnational-cancer-institute-fTQHPb6r4wQ-unsplash-1024x683.jpg%201024w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-684314%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22800%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EAntibiotics%20are%20used%20for%20longer%20than%20needed%20and%20sometimes%20the%20wrong%20type%20is%20used.%20Photo%3A%20National%20Cancer%20Institute%2FUnsplash%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20some%20situations%2C%20this%20is%20understandable.%20Infections%20in%20different%20body%20sites%20are%20usually%20due%20to%20different%20types%20of%20bacteria.%20When%20the%20diagnosis%20isn%E2%80%99t%20certain%2C%20we%20often%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fonlinelibrary.wiley.com%2Fdoi%2Ffull%2F10.1111%2Fresp.13334%5C%22%3Eerr%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%20the%20side%20of%20caution%20by%20giving%20broad%20spectrum%20antibiotics%20to%20make%20sure%20we%20have%20active%20treatments%20for%20all%20possible%20infections%2C%20until%20further%20information%20becomes%20available.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20other%20situations%2C%20there%20is%20a%20degree%20of%20inertia.%20If%20the%20patient%20is%20improving%2C%20doctors%20tend%20to%20simply%20continue%20the%20same%20treatment%2C%20rather%20than%20change%20to%20more%20appropriate%20choice.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20general%20practice%2C%20the%20issue%20of%20diagnostic%20uncertainty%20and%20therapeutic%20inertia%20are%20often%20magnified.%20Patients%20who%20recover%20after%20starting%20antibiotics%20don%E2%80%99t%20usually%20require%20tests%20or%20come%20back%20for%20review%2C%20so%20there%20is%20no%20easy%20way%20of%20knowing%20if%20the%20antibiotic%20was%20actually%20required.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAntibiotic%20prescribing%20can%20be%20more%20complex%20again%20if%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.mja.com.au%2Fjournal%2F2014%2F201%2F2%2Fantibiotic-prescribing-practice-residential-aged-care-facilities-health-care%5C%22%3Epatients%3C%2Fa%3E%20are%20expecting%20%E2%80%9Ca%20pill%20for%20every%20ill%E2%80%9D.%20While%20doctors%20are%20generally%20good%20at%20educating%20patients%20when%20antibiotics%20are%20not%20likely%20to%20work%20(for%20example%2C%20for%20viral%20infections)%2C%20without%20confirmatory%20tests%20there%20can%20always%20be%20a%20lingering%20doubt%20in%20the%20minds%20of%20both%20doctors%20and%20patients.%20Or%20sometimes%20the%20patient%20goes%20elsewhere%20to%20find%20a%20prescription.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFor%20other%20infections%2C%20resistance%20can%20develop%20if%20treatments%20aren%E2%80%99t%20given%20for%20long%20enough.%20This%20is%20particularly%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fpubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov%2F11971765%2F%5C%22%3Ecase%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20tuberculosis%2C%20caused%20by%20a%20slow%20growing%20bacterium%20that%20requires%20a%20particularly%20long%20course%20of%20antibiotics%20to%20cure.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20in%20humans%2C%20antibiotics%20are%20also%20used%20to%20prevent%20and%20treat%20infections%20in%20animals.%20However%2C%20a%20proportion%20of%20antibiotics%20are%20used%20for%20growth%20promotion.%20In%20Australia%2C%20an%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.mja.com.au%2Fjournal%2F2019%2F211%2F4%2Fantibiotic-use-animals-and-humans-australia%5C%22%3Eestimated%3C%2Fa%3E%2060%25%20of%20antibiotics%20were%20used%20in%20animals%20between%202005-2010%2C%20despite%20growth-promotion%20being%20phased%20out.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhy%20is%20overuse%20a%20problem%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBacteria%20become%20resistant%20to%20the%20effect%20of%20antibiotics%20through%20natural%20selection%20%E2%80%93%20those%20that%20survive%20exposure%20to%20antibiotics%20are%20the%20strains%20that%20have%20a%20mechanism%20to%20evade%20their%20effects.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFor%20example%2C%20antibiotics%20are%20sometimes%20given%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thelancet.com%2Fjournals%2Flaninf%2Farticle%2FPIIS1473-3099(18)30279-2%2Ffulltext%5C%22%3Eprevent%3C%2Fa%3E%20recurrent%20urinary%20tract%20infections%2C%20but%20a%20consequence%2C%20any%20infection%20that%20does%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Facademic.oup.com%2Fcid%2Farticle%2F73%2F3%2Fe782%2F6141409%5C%22%3Edevelop%3C%2Fa%3E%20tends%20to%20be%20with%20resistant%20bacteria.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhen%20resistance%20to%20the%20commonly%20used%20first-line%20antibiotics%20occurs%2C%20we%20often%20need%20to%20reach%20deeper%20into%20the%20bag%20to%20find%20other%20effective%20treatments.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESome%20of%20these%20last-line%20antibiotics%20are%20those%20that%20had%20been%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov%2Fpmc%2Farticles%2FPMC4202707%2F%5C%22%3Esuperseded%3C%2Fa%3E%20because%20they%20had%20serious%20side%20effects%20or%20couldn%E2%80%99t%20be%20given%20conveniently%20as%20tablets.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENew%20drugs%20for%20some%20bacteria%20have%20been%20developed%2C%20but%20many%20are%20much%20more%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov%2Fpmc%2Farticles%2FPMC7955006%2F%5C%22%3Eexpensive%3C%2Fa%3E%20than%20older%20ones.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ETreating%20antibiotics%20as%20a%20valuable%20resource%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20concept%20of%20antibiotics%20as%20a%20valuable%20resource%20has%20led%20to%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fpubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov%2F8856755%2F%5C%22%3Econcept%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20%E2%80%9Cantimicrobial%20stewardship%E2%80%9D%2C%20with%20programs%20to%20promote%20the%20responsible%20use%20of%20antibiotics.%20It%E2%80%99s%20a%20similar%20concept%20to%20environmental%20stewardship%20to%20prevent%20climate%20change%20and%20environmental%20degradation.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAntibiotics%20are%20a%20rare%20class%20of%20medication%20where%20treatment%20of%20one%20patient%20can%20potentially%20affect%20the%20outcome%20of%20other%20patients%2C%20through%20the%20transmission%20of%20antibiotic%20resistant%20bacteria.%20Therefore%2C%20like%20efforts%20to%20combat%20climate%20change%2C%20antibiotic%20stewardship%20relies%20on%20changing%20individual%20actions%20to%20benefit%20the%20broader%20community.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELike%20climate%20change%2C%20antibiotic%20resistance%20is%20a%20complex%20problem%20when%20seen%20in%20a%20broader%20context.%20Studies%20have%20linked%20resistance%20to%20the%20values%20and%20priorities%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thelancet.com%2Fjournals%2Flanplh%2Farticle%2FPIIS2542-5196(18)30186-4%2Ffulltext%5C%22%3Eof%20governments%3C%2Fa%3E%20such%20as%20corruption%20and%20infrastructure%2C%20including%20the%20availability%20of%20electricity%20and%20public%20services.%20This%20highlights%20that%20there%20are%20broader%20%E2%80%9Ccauses%20of%20the%20causes%E2%80%9D%2C%20such%20as%20public%20spending%20on%20sanitation%20and%20health%20care.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOther%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Facademic.oup.com%2Fjac%2Farticle%2F74%2F9%2F2803%2F5512029%3Flogin%3Dtrue%5C%22%3Estudies%3C%2Fa%3E%20have%20suggested%20individuals%20need%20to%20be%20considered%20within%20the%20broader%20social%20and%20institutional%20influences%20on%20prescribing%20behaviour.%20Like%20all%20human%20behaviour%2C%20antibiotic%20prescribing%20is%20complicated%2C%20and%20factors%20like%20what%20doctors%20feel%20is%20%E2%80%9Cnormal%E2%80%9D%20prescribing%2C%20whether%20junior%20staff%20feel%20they%20can%20challenge%20senior%20doctors%2C%20and%20even%20their%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nytimes.com%2F2016%2F10%2F07%2Fupshot%2Fyour-surgeon-is-probably-a-republican-your-psychiatrist-probably-a-democrat.html%5C%22%3Epolitical%20views%3C%2Fa%3E%20may%20be%20important.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThere%20are%20also%20issues%20with%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.cambridge.org%2Fcore%2Fjournals%2Finternational-journal-of-technology-assessment-in-health-care%2Farticle%2Fvalue-assessment-of-antimicrobials-and-the-implications-for-development-access-and-funding-of-effective-treatments-australian-stakeholder-perspective%2FD45758CFB95520DA4FF06E46135E0628%5C%22%3Eeconomic%20model%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20developing%20new%20antibiotics.%20When%20a%20new%20antibiotic%20is%20first%20approved%20for%20use%2C%20the%20first%20reaction%20for%20prescribers%20is%20not%20to%20use%20it%2C%20whether%20to%20ensure%20it%20retains%20its%20effectiveness%20or%20because%20it%20is%20often%20very%20expensive.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20this%20doesn%E2%80%99t%20really%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Facademic.oup.com%2Fcid%2Farticle%2F50%2F8%2F1081%2F449089%3Flogin%3Dtrue%5C%22%3Eencourage%3C%2Fa%3E%20the%20development%20of%20new%20antibiotics%2C%20particularly%20when%20pharma%20research%20and%20development%20budgets%20can%20easily%20be%20diverted%20to%20developing%20drugs%20for%20conditions%20patients%20take%20for%20years%2C%20rather%20than%20a%20few%20days.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20slow%20moving%20pandemic%20of%20resistance%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CIf%20we%20fail%20to%20act%2C%20we%20are%20looking%20at%20an%20almost%20unthinkable%20scenario%20where%20antibiotics%20no%20longer%20work%20and%20we%20are%20cast%20back%20into%20the%20dark%20ages%20of%20medicine%2C%E2%80%9D%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Famr-review.org%2F%5C%22%3EDavid%20Cameron%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20former%20UK%20Prime%20Minister%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAntibiotic%20resistance%20is%20already%20a%20problem.%20Almost%20all%20infectious%20diseases%20physicians%20have%20had%20the%20dreaded%20call%20about%20patients%20with%20infections%20that%20were%20essentially%20untreatable%2C%20or%20where%20they%20had%20to%20scramble%20to%20find%20supplies%20of%20long-forgotten%20last-line%20antibiotics.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThere%20are%20already%20hospitals%20in%20some%20parts%20of%20the%20world%20that%20have%20had%20to%20carefully%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.reactgroup.org%2Fnews-and-views%2Fnews-and-opinions%2Fyear-2022%2Fthe-impact-of-antibiotic-resistance-on-cancer-treatment-especially-in-low-and-middle-income-countries-and-the-way-forward%2F%5C%22%3Econsider%3C%2Fa%3E%20whether%20it%E2%80%99s%20still%20viable%20to%20treat%20cancers%2C%20because%20of%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov%2Fpmc%2Farticles%2FPMC6276316%2F%5C%22%3Ehigh%20risk%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20infections%20with%20antibiotic-resistant%20bacteria.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20global%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thelancet.com%2Fjournals%2Flancet%2Farticle%2FPIIS0140-6736(21)02724-0%2Ffulltext%5C%22%3Estudy%3C%2Fa%3E%20estimated%20that%20in%202019%2C%20almost%205%20million%20deaths%20occurred%20with%20an%20infection%20involving%20antibiotic-resistant%20bacteria.%20Some%201.3%20million%20would%20not%20have%20occurred%20if%20the%20bacteria%20were%20not%20resistant.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20UK%E2%80%99s%202014%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Famr-review.org%2Fsites%2Fdefault%2Ffiles%2FAMR%2520Review%2520Paper%2520-%2520Tackling%2520a%2520crisis%2520for%2520the%2520health%2520and%2520wealth%2520of%2520nations_1.pdf%5C%22%3EO%E2%80%99Neill%20report%3C%2Fa%3E%20predicted%20deaths%20from%20antimicrobial%20resistance%20could%20rise%20to%2010%20million%20deaths%20each%20year%2C%20and%20cost%202-3.5%25%20of%20global%20GDP%2C%20by%202050%20based%20on%20trends%20at%20that%20time.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhat%20can%20we%20do%20about%20it%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThere%20is%20a%20lot%20we%20can%20do%20to%20prevent%20antibiotic%20resistance.%20We%20can%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cul%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.marketingmag.com.au%2Fnews%2Ffilm-picking-gonorrhoea-wins-tropfest-prize%2F%5C%22%3Eraise%3C%2Fa%3E%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fbmcpublichealth.biomedcentral.com%2Farticles%2F10.1186%2Fs12889-019-7258-3%5C%22%3Eawareness%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20many%20infections%20will%20get%20better%20by%20themselves%2C%20and%20don%E2%80%99t%20necessarily%20need%20antibiotics%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3Euse%20the%20antibiotics%2