Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ED-Day%20on%20film%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Normandy%20invasion%20has%20been%20subject%20of%20various%20films%2C%20perhaps%20most%20famously%20%3Cem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.imdb.com%2Ftitle%2Ftt0056197%2F%3Fref_%3Dfn_al_tt_1%5C%22%3EThe%20Longest%20Day%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%20(1962).%20In%20the%20modern%20era%2C%20however%2C%20the%20D-Day%20film%20of%20most%20renown%20is%20undoubtedly%20Stephen%20Spielberg%E2%80%99s%20%3Cem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.imdb.com%2Ftitle%2Ftt0120815%2F%5C%22%3ESaving%20Private%20Ryan%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%20(1998)%2C%20which%20starred%20Tom%20Hanks%20and%20Matt%20Damon.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cdiv%3E%3Ciframe%20width%3D%5C%22100%25%5C%22%20allowfullscreen%3D%5C%22allowfullscreen%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.youtube.com%2Fembed%2F9CiW_DgxCnQ%3Fwmode%3Dtransparent%26start%3D0%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22504%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fiframe%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIntended%20as%20a%20homage%20to%20the%20%E2%80%9C%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.britannica.com%2Ftopic%2FGreatest-Generation%5C%22%3Egreatest%20generation%3C%2Fa%3E%E2%80%9D%2C%20the%20film%20begins%20with%20an%20old%20soldier%20(the%20titular%20Private%20Ryan)%20searching%20the%20graves%20in%20the%20vast%20American%20military%20cemetery%20overlooking%20Omaha%20Beach%20in%20Normandy.%20This%20was%20the%20scene%20of%20some%20of%20the%20deadliest%20fighting%20on%20June%206%201944.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFinding%20the%20grave%20he%20is%20looking%20for%2C%20the%20aged%20veteran%20drops%20to%20his%20knees%20before%20the%20camera%20zooms%20in%20on%20his%20eyes%20so%20that%20Spielberg%20can%20take%20us%20back%20to%20the%20battle%20on%20that%20grey%20spring%20morning.%20It%20is%20a%20powerful%20scene%2C%20and%20it%20has%20clearly%20inspired%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Great%20Escaper%3C%2Fem%3E%E2%80%99s%20director%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.history.co.uk%2Farticles%2Ftheres-a-lot-of-deep-deep-feeling-director-oliver-parker-on-his-new-film-the-great-escaper%5C%22%3EOliver%20Parker%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIndeed%2C%20the%20shadow%20of%20%3Cem%3ESaving%20Private%20Ryan%3C%2Fem%3E%20looms%20large%20throughout.%20Like%20Spielberg%2C%20Parker%20takes%20us%20back%20to%20a%20Normandy%20burial%20ground%2C%20this%20time%20the%20Commonwealth%20War%20Graves%20Commission%20Cemetery%20in%20the%20town%20of%20Bayeux.%20He%20has%20us%20wander%20among%20the%20serried%20ranks%20of%20headstones%20and%2C%20via%20a%20series%20of%20flashbacks%2C%20we%20witness%20the%20carnage%20on%20the%20coast%20in%20washed-out%20colour%2C%20with%20the%20salt%20and%20sea%20spray%20in%20our%20eyes.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThese%20similarities%2C%20I%20think%2C%20reveal%20the%20ultimate%20point%20of%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Great%20Escaper%3C%2Fem%3E.%20Through%20the%20familiar%20trope%20of%20a%20war-damaged%20British%20veteran%2C%20the%20film%20pays%20homage%20to%20those%20who%20fought%20and%20won%20the%20Second%20World%20War.%20It%E2%80%99s%20a%20generation%20much%20vaunted%20in%20recent%20years%2C%20especially%20amid%20all%20the%20Brexit-induced%20forties%20nostalgia.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20doing%20so%2C%20Caine%E2%80%99s%20filmic%20finale%20also%20delivers%20an%20assertive%20British%20claim%20on%20the%20memory%20of%20D-Day%20(complete%20with%20obligatory%20digs%20at%20the%20%E2%80%9Clateness%E2%80%9D%20to%20the%20conflict%20of%20the%20American%20ally).%20In%20effect%2C%20it%20is%20the%20cinematic%20counterpart%20to%20the%20new%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.britishnormandymemorial.org%5C%22%3EBritish%20Normandy%20War%20Memorial%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20unveiled%20just%20two%20years%20ago%20in%20June%202021.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhether%20or%20not%20Parker%E2%80%99s%20film%20goes%20on%20to%20have%20the%20same%20cultural%20impact%20as%20Spielberg%E2%80%99s%20award-winning%20production%20remains%20to%20be%20seen.%20But%20thanks%20to%20the%20powerful%20presence%20of%20Michael%20Caine%20it%20surely%20stands%20a%20decent%20chance.%3C%2Fp